 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Flight TWA 800 blown up </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Flight TWA 800 blown up </b><br><br><br><b><h2>19 July 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Terror or accident?</h2><h3>  Reports claim Arab group warned of attack on US target before 230 killed</h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Jonathan Freedland</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>The sudden catastrophe which overtook TWA Flight 800 off Long Island, New York, on wednesday night  killing all 230 people on board has cast a long, fearful shadow over today's formal opening of the  Olympic Games in Atlanta. As investigators, backed by local fishermen, scoured the crash site about 10  miles south of Moriches Bay for bodies and wreckage of the Boeing 747 jumbo jet, speculation that it  had been destroyed deliberately intensified late last night amid reports that before the blast an  Arabic newspaper had been warned of an attack by the same group that claimed responsibility for an  earlier bombing in Saudi Arabia.  <p>  <p>According to ABC News, the Movement for Islamic Change - which claimed it was behind the killing of  five Americans in Riyadh last November - warned the al-Hayat Arabic paper on Wednesday that a US  target would be hit at the exact time Flight 800 went down.  <p>  <p>The warning used "chilling specifics", ABC said, but was not passed on to authorities.  <p>  <p>"All will be surprised by the size of the attack, the place and the time," the group warned.  <p>  <p>Citing sources close to the investigation, ABC said the leading theory was that the airliner was  destroyed by extremists using a shoulder-fired anti-aircraft missile.  <p>  <p>Earlier, before news of the reports, President Clinton in a nationally televised press conference  emphatically warned against making any assumptions about the cause of the crash.  <p>  <p>"We do not know what caused this tragedy," Mr Clinton said. "We will determine what happened [but]  I caution you all against jumping to conclusions."  <p>  <p>The United States navy moved swiftly to the scene, with spokesmen expressing confidence that  crucial evidence contained in the 'black box' flight recorders could be recovered. The National  Transportation Safety Board last night denied a report that one had been found.  <p>  <p>Conflicting pieces of evidence surfaced yesterday - some suggesting terror, some indicating an  accident.  <p>  <p>TWA officials said the crew included two veteran pilots, flying a plane with a near-flawless safety  record. No passenger Boeing 747 has ever crashed due to a mechanical fault.  <p>  <p>They also noted that there had been no radio alert from the cockpit, and that no inflated  life-rafts or life-jackets had been found - suggesting an instant blast rather than a lingering  technical problem.  <p>  <p>Terrorism experts also noted that the flight had taken off from Athens, which until mid-May was  deemed by US authorities to have lax airport security. Pentagon officials also acknowledged that US  fears of terrorist attacks have been rising since last month's blast at an American barracks outside  Dhahran, Saudi Arabia, which killed 19 military personnel. Speculation was also fuelled by claims the  plane was delayed because of a fault in a key instrument, the engine pressure-ratio gauge. While in  itself not a potential cause of an accident, such a fault could have indicated a problem with engine  power.  <p>  <p>The TWA flight left John F Kennedy airport on Long Island bound for Charles de Gaulle, Paris, at  about 8.19pm local time on Wednesday. It apparently exploded 29 minutes later at an altitude of  13,000ft, plunging swiftly into the sea. Some witnesses spoke of a brilliant spiral, like a fireworks  display.  <p>  <p>After many hours of searching in the darkness, all hopes of survivors faded. More than half the  bodies had been recovered yesterday, and officials conceded it was near-impossible that anyone had  survived.  <p>  <p>Details of who was aboard and where they came from were not released by TWA as it notified next of  kin. Early today the airline revised to 230 the number of passengers and crew on board.  <p>  <p>Some information emerged elsewhere. One of the victims was named by the Italian foreign ministry as  Christine Baily, a Briton who had emigrated to Italy. It was reported she was married to an Italian,  Pietro D'Iorio, and that the pair worked as waiters in Prato, near Florence.  <p>  <p>Two newly-wed Italian couples returning from a honeymoon in the US were among those killed.  <p>  <p>At his press conference, Mr Clinton singled out 16 teenagers from Montoursville High School,  Pennsylvania, who were on board Flight 800 on their way to a language course in Paris.  <p>  <p>"The whole town is in mourning," said John Doring, Montoursville's mayor. "These kids were the best  of the best."  <p>  <p>Distraught relatives gathered in holding rooms set aside at John F Kennedy airport and at Charles  de Gaulle as they waited for news. TWA yesterday released the names of Flight 800's crew.  <p>  <p>Despite Mr Clinton's caution, the FBI and the New York Police Department launched a joint  anti-terrorist task force and declared the 200-mile area a crime scene. Pentagon and state department  counter-terrorism experts joined the investigation. The National Transportation Safety Board team was  conducting a parallel inquiry.  <p>  <p>Officials in Atlanta ordered security, already tight for today's start of the Olympics, to be  stepped up. A 25,000-strong security force is in the city, the largest-ever assembled in the US in  peacetime.  <p>  <p>Details of the plane's last hours - after 25 years in service - began to emerge last night. After  arriving in New York from Athens, and being cleared of passengers and cargo, it took off after being  delayed for an hour by a late-arriving passenger and a fault on the baggage-loading belt. Less than  half an hour later, witnesses saw a flame shoot from the plane like a flare, the aircraft dropped for  a few seconds and then blew up. "There was a huge fireball," said Maureen Cassidy, a waitress who was  serving dinner. "It was just flames and black smoke and it was just pouring out of the sky."  <p>  <p>A TWA spokesman said the plane disappeared from radar at 8.48pm. A flotilla of boats gathered at  the scene, where burning wreckage and fuel lit up the night sky. In daylight, coastguard cutters  recovered a 30ft piece of fuselage, wing tips and a large piece of the plane's tail. Rescue workers  found dozens of bodies, some still strapped into their seats, as well as rucksacks, suitcases and  wallets. One letter was recovered, still legible: it was from a mother, writing to her daughter at  summer camp.   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <