 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Fifty-one children hurt as bus loses roof under bridge in  Runcorn, Cheshire </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Fifty-one children hurt as bus loses roof under bridge in Runcorn, Cheshire  </b><br><br><br><b><h2>19 July 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Fifty-one children hurt as bus loses roof under  bridge  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Nick Varley</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>A school outing ended in horror last night when a double-decker bus carrying 73 pupils home  ploughed into a low bridge in Runcorn, Cheshire. Fifty-one children, mostly aged 10 and 11, and three  adults - one a man believed to be the driver - were taken to hospital after the upper floor of the  vehicle was ripped off in the accident.  <p>  <p>None was seriously hurt. Thirty-three of the children suffered minor injuries and the 18 more  seriously hurt escaped without broken bones or major organ injuries. None of the adults was seriously  hurt. Eight casualties were expected to be operated on last night but Warrington general hospital  accident and emergency consultant director, Arfan Saleh, stressed none of the patients was in a  critical condition.  <p>  <p>"Some of the children have serious scalp lacerations with loss of skin and some just have ordinary  cuts," he said. "There are two minor eye injuries." The accident happened as pupils and staff from  Palace Fields primary school, Runcorn, were returning from the Waterworld theme park in  Stoke-on-Trent. The bus struck a concrete and iron pedestrian bridge, coming to rest, roofless, 30  yards away.  <p>  <p>Richard Oswick, of Mersey regional ambulance, said: "The first 20 paramedics arrived to find the  entire top deck of the double-decker bus had been ripped off.  <p>  <p>"It was appalling. Everyone had got off the bus, and the injured children were lying on the grass  verge being looked after by those who weren't hurt. The remains of the bus are a crumpled mess below  the bridge." Pupil Lisa Brigden, aged 11, who was on the top deck, said: "The bus wasn't travelling  fast but there was no warning. Suddenly there was a big bang and the roof just ripped off over our  heads. There was glass everywhere and the roof was missing. Everyone was screaming and there was blood on  our hands and clothes."  <p>  <p>Barbara Lewis, aged 38, who made the trip with her daughter Donna, aged 11, as a parent helper,  said: "It could have been much worse.  <p>  <p>"If it had been a bus full of adults rather than children there would have been fatalities but  because they are small the bridge skimmed over their heads."  <p>  <p>Twenty-two pupils were unharmed in the accident and were taken back to school to be met by anxious  parents.  <p>  <p>Police inquiries into the accident were centred on why the bus was travelling in a lane designed  for only single-decker vehicles. Cheshire county councillor Bill Foster said: "There are several  unanswered questions here, but the main one is what made this bus turn on to this busway. It was only  ever designed for single-decker buses and I have never heard of an accident like this before."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
