 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Save the World Service campaign</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Save the World Service campaign</b><br><br><br><b><h2>19 July 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Save the World Service - MPs vent fury at Birt's radical plans</h2><h3>Hanley admits Foreign Office disappointment at being  given just 24 hours notice of changes, as Labour calls for idea to be put on hold</h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Rebecca Smithers</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>The future of the BBC World Service dominated parliamentary proceedings yesterday, as MPs and peers  vented their fury over the radical changes planned by the BBC.  <p>  <p>In the Lords, the Government narrowly averted defeat by a majority of just 10, after peers voted by  81 to 71 against a call by the Commons to reconsider the privatisation of transmission services under  the Broadcasting Bill.  <p>  <p>A division was forced on an amendment to the legislation as a device to put pressure on ministers  to intervene to stop the wide-ranging changes planned for the station.  <p>  <p>In the Commons committee corridor, MPs had two separate inquisitions of ministers and BBC managers.  Foreign Office minister Jeremy Hanley admitted that his department was "disappointed" that it was  given just 24 hours notice by the BBC of its plans to merge the World Service English language news  with mainstream BBC news and current affairs coverage.  <p>  <p>But he insisted that Labour was wrong in its claims that no consultation was taking place, and that  such an exercise was well under way.  <p>  <p>The meeting next Wednesday between BBC chiefs Sir Christopher Bland and John Birt and the Foreign  Secretary, Malcolm Rifkind, is part of that process, when the proposals will be discussed in detail.  <p>  <p>Yesterday, questioned by MPs on the cross-party foreign affairs select committee, Mr Hanley  admitted that his department had the "ultimate sanction" if it was not happy with the plans, by  withdrawing the &#163;175m a year funding which supports the scheme.  <p>  <p>Mr Hanley said that, although there had been no room for ministerial comment or discussion when the  BBC alerted the Foreign Office to its proposals just a day before they were published, it had been  agreed that there would be "full consultation" on the plans before they came into force. "The Foreign  Office will not allow the standard to fall," Mr Hanley told MPs on the committee.  <p>  <p>"It is absolutely vital that the distinctive nature and quality of the World Service continues and  that is our pledge."  <p>  <p>Later, at business questions in the afternoon, the shadow leader of the House, Ann Taylor, urged  the Government to consider delaying a final decision on the future of the World Service until  Parliament had had a chance to debate the issue - probably not until after the summer recess. But the  Leader of the House, Tony Newton, said he accepted that the future of the World Service was "not  simply an operational matter" and pointed out that Mr Rifkind was intending to have discussions with  the BBC next week. Mr Hanley had earlier sought to calm MPs angry at the lack of notice about the  changes given to his department by the BBC's management.   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
