 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Businessmen paying up to £100,000 to dine with  Major</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Businessmen paying up to £100,000 to dine with Major</b><br><br><br><b><h2>23 July  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Mawhinney defends PM dining club donations</h2><h3> Businessmen pay  thousands for dinners "in the nation's interest"</h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David Hencke</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Brian Mawhinney, the Conservative Party chairman, yesterday claimed businessmen paying up to  &#163;100,000 to dine with John Major were donating to the Tories in the "nation's interest".  <p>  <p>His defence came as Labour and Liberal Democrats baited ministers in the Commons and Lords over the  Observer newspaper's disclosure of the existence of the Premier Club - a dining club with a minimum  &#163;10,000 a year subscription guaranteeing dinners with cabinet ministers.  <p>  <p>Mr Mawhinney was replying to Robin Cook, who accused the Conservatives of "corruption" after it was  disclosed that property developer John Beckwith, chairman of the Premier Club, has a leading role in a  consortium shortlisted to buy Ministry of Defence homes.  <p>  <p>Mr Mawhinney told Mr Cook: "Those who choose to give money to the Conservative Party do so not  because they receive influence in return, but because they believe that a Conservative government  would be in the nation's interest.  <p>  <p>"There is no question of anyone buying or selling access to the Prime Minister or indeed any other  minister, for any sum."  <p>  <p>Ministers compared the Premier Club to Labour's &#163;1000 club, pointing out that both parties had  private lists of donors, which in Labour's case would not be declared until after the election.  <p>  <p>The Deputy Prime Minister, Michael Heseltine, drew Tory laughter in the Commons yesterday as he  told MPs that people had to pay &#163;430 to dine with Tony Blair at London's Savoy Hotel. He said  that the higher figure suggested in media reports for eating with Mr Major reflected "the quality of  the two individuals".   <p>  <p>Lord Mackay of Ardbrecknish in the Lords took a similar tack when challenged by  Lord Avebury, the Liberal Democrat peer. Labour's Derek Foster protested to Roger Freeman, the public  service minister, that plans to privatise Her Majesty's Stationery Office had become "a car boot sale  of Civil Service jobs, a handout of public sector assets and contacts - and some to your fat-cat  friends payrolling the Tory Party through the Premier Club".  <p>  <p>The issue resurfaced during exchanges on Government plans to suspend the Post Office monopoly.  Labour pressed the President of the Board of Trade, Ian Lang, for assurances that no one would benefit  from the lifting of the monopoly "through any company whose members have paid large amounts of money"  to dine with him or the Prime Minister. Mr Lang avoided giving a direct reply.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
