 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - 4,000 frozen human embryos to be destroyed</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>4,000 frozen human embryos to be destroyed</b><br><br><br><b><h2>23 July  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Frozen human embryos to be destroyed</h2><h3>Parents cannot be found as 4,000 fertilised  eggs face deadline</h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Chris Mihill</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Up to 4,000 frozen embryos from about 900 couples are to be destroyed at the end of the month  because the parents cannot be contacted, have shown no interest in the fate of their potential  children or do not want them any more.  <p>  <p>The destruction has to take place because Parliament said in 1990 that, from August 1991, embryos  could be frozen only for five years, meaning the deadline is up on 31 July. In May the regulations  were changed so that embryos could be stored for 10 years, but only if the parents were contacted and  gave their permission.  <p>  <p>Ruth Deech, chairwoman of the Human Fertilisation and Embryology Authority, which regulates clinics  holding the embryos, said yesterday: "The regulations allow many patients to extend their consent to  10 years or more in some exceptional cases. But if that consent cannot be obtained the storage has to  cease, which means, sadly, allowing a number of embryos to perish.  <p>  <p>"But if you think through the other options - of using them without the consent of the individuals,  or of keeping them stored indefinitely - those options are far less acceptable.  Some have suggested that these embryos should be donated or 'adopted'. This would be wrong both  legally and ethically."  <p>  <p>Dr Peter Brinsden, the medical director of Bourn Hall, Cambridge, which pioneered in vitro  fertilisation treatment, said the centre had 265 couples it could not contact covering 904 embryos,  out of 10,000 in storage. "It would be completely unethical to use the embryos for purposes other than  originally intended by the couples."  <p>  <p>A spokeman for Issue, the infertility pressure group, said: "It would be ideal if these embryos  could be used for other infertile couples, but the ownership remains with the parents. We find it sad  they must be destroyed, but the law is the law."  <p>  <p>The embryology authority said about 9,000 embryos faced the five-year deadline. Of these, 2,100  embryos from 650 couples would perish because it had not been possible to contact the parents; another  1,200 embryos from 260 couples would be destroyed because the parents had been contacted but did not  reply.  <p>  <p>About 10 per cent of the parents that have been contacted by clinics have said they no longer want  their embryos stored, meaning the final number to be destroyed is likely to be around 4,000.  <p>  <p>Most frozen embryos are just four cells. They will be brought out of storage, allowed to reach room  temperature and then destroyed with a drop of water or alcohol.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
