 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - 54 Hebridean islanders fight to buy their island,  Eigg</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>54 Hebridean islanders fight to buy their island, Eigg</b><br><br><br><b><h2>26 July  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Eigg seeks to throw off 'feudal' yoke  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Nick Varley</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>The estate agent, a self-styled 'dealer in mother nature's artwork', described his latest property  as 'one of her masterpieces'.  <p>  <p>But to inhabitants of the tiny Hebridean island of Eigg, such romance has worn off as their home is  put up for sale for the second time in 15 months. The move is the latest twist in a saga almost as  surreal as the paintings of its owner, Marlin Eckhard, an amateur artist with the brush-name Maruma  who promised &#163;15m investment on a new ferry, housing, hotel and pier. In fact, nothing has changed since his second and last visit over a year ago.  <p>  <p>Now Eigg's 54 inhabitants are hoping to buy the 15 square mile island, lying between Rhum and Muck  12 miles off the Scottish coast, for less than the 'simply unrealistic' &#163;2m asking price.  <p>  <p>Maggie Fyffe, the islanders' spokeswoman, said: "This is the turning point. Something has to happen  now. We will be pulling out all the stops to get a package together to make an offer for the island.  We will make it quite clear we do not want another private owner and that we want to take control  of our own futures."  <p>  <p>Such a move would mean the end of private ownership dating back to 1308, and owners ranging from a  former Times journalist to ex-Olympic bobsleigher Keith Schellenberg.  Mr Schellenberg, who residents thought as feudal a laird as any in the centuries before, sold to  Maruma after 20 years' rule which ended in open hostility with them. Hopes that the new owner would be  more agreeable were swiftly dashed.  <p>  <p>Mrs Fyffe said: "He was not reliable in any way, shape or form. We have had a very bad experience  here."  <p>  <p>The islanders' bid for ownership is being backed by the Scottish Wildlife Trust, whose director,  Alasdair Sutherland, said: "Our prime consideration is the conservation of the unique range of  habitats on the island and the welfare of the species there.  <p>  <p>"But I am confident we will be able to mount a successful bid for Eigg and finally decide its  future. It would take a very stupid or thick-skinned individual to follow Maruma there now."  <p>  <p>Farhad Vladi, a Hamburg-based Austrian dealer in islands who handled the sale to Maruma last year,  has been called in again to assist local estate agents.  He wished the islanders every success in their campaign but dashed any hopes the laird might sell  to them at a knockdown price, saying they only had themselves, and the press, to blame.  <p>  <p>He said: "The reason Herr Maruma is selling is because he is very disappointed at the treatment he  received from them and the British press. Why should he give them preferential treatment?"  <p>  <p>Maruma was unavailable for comment last night.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
