 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Rioch dismissed two weeks after signing contract as Arsenal manager </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Rioch dismissed two weeks after signing contract as Arsenal manager  </b><br><br><br><b><h2>27 August 1996</h2></b><br><h2>City eye Rioch as Ball quits   </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Ian Ross</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>English football's new season claimed another major casualty last night with the resignation of the  Manchester City manager Alan Ball. The First Division club are now expected to make a formal approach  to Bruce Rioch, who was controversially dismissed as the manager of Arsenal a fortnight ago. Ball's  brief and turbulent reign at Maine Road came to an abrupt end after an early evening meeting with his  chairman Francis Lee to discuss his future in the wake of City's disappointing start to the new  season. After being relegated from the Premiership in May with only nine victories, City have won just  one of their opening three fixtures so far. On Saturday, during and after a 2-1 defeat by Stoke City,  Ball was barracked by a large section of the City support.  <p>  <p>Although he insisted after that game that he had no intention of resigning he spent the weekend  discussing his future with his family before meeting Lee for talks.  <p>  <p>The club secretary Bernard Halford last night issued a short statement: "A meeting was held tonight  at which Mr Alan Ball tendered his resignation as manager of Manchester City football club which was  accepted. The chairman and board would like to place on record their appreciation of his endeavours  and efforts whilst in his period of office and wish him well in the future." Ball was appointed in  July of last year in succession to Brian Horton, now the manager of Huddersfield Town.  <p>  <p>Sadly for the 1996 World Cup winner, the management record of 51-year-old Ball has never matched  his progress as a player.  Only one of six clubs under his charge, Southampton, have avoided relegation. He entered League  management with Blackpool, his first club as a player, before moving on to Portsmouth, where he  enjoyed his sole promotion - to the old First Division in 1987 - before moving on to Stoke and Exeter.  Southampton, another of his former clubs, recalled him to the top flight in 1994 and at The Dell he  fought successful battles against relegation for two seasons. But last summer he could not resist a  return to the North-west and the challenge at Maine Road.  <p>  <p>Elsewhere, Neil Ruddock will shortly become Britain's most expensive defender when he leaves  Liverpool. Leeds are expected to be first in the queue to sign the England centre-back who handed in a  written transfer request on Saturday after learning he was not in the team to play Sunderland at  Anfield.  <p>  <p>Roy Evans insisted yesterday he had no great desire to sell Ruddock, but Liverpool have always  acceded to the wishes of players making written requests to leave.  <p>  <p>"I have received Neil's request and it will be considered in due course," said Evans. "He does know  that I want to keep him here but I shall look at all aspects of the situation. I can fully understand  his sense of frustration at being out of the first team at the moment but that is a problem a manager  will always face."  <p>  <p>Leeds are expected to make their move, possibly before the weekend. Liverpool will almost certainly  receive more than &#163;5m for Ruddock, who joined from Tottenham for &#163;2.6m in 1992. Rangers, Arsenal and Newcastle are also  likely to be interested.  <p>  <p>Manchester United's Nicky Butt (thigh) and Chelsea's Jody Morris (ankle) are out of the England  Under-21 squad for Saturday's game in Moldova. Leicester City's Emile Heskey (hamstring) is doubtful  and Everton's 17-year-old striker Michael Branch has been called up as cover.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG