 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Beat-a-cheat hotline service attracts more than 1,500 calls on its first day </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Beat-a-cheat hotline service is launched attracting more than 1,500 calls on  its first day </b><br><br><br><b><h2>6 August 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Early rush for Lilley's cheat line   </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David Brindle</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>More than 1,500 callers yesterday used a new freephone service for people to inform on suspected  benefit cheats on its first day of operation. Within minutes of Peter Lilley, the Social Security  Secretary, launching the scheme, lines on the 'beat-a-cheat' were ringing. By the end of the day 1,654  people had registered their suspicions.  <p>  <p>A spokesman for the department said: "It was very good for a short day." The line opened after Mr  Lilley unveiled it at 11pm and ran until 6.30pm. From now on it will operate from 8.30am to 6.30pm  daily. Ministers are expecting 2,000 calls a day after an inital rush of 20,000 a week. At the  hotline's launch Mr Lilley announced record savings from "fraud and benefit incorrectness" of  &#163;1.44bn in 1995/96. Excluding housing benefit savings by local authorities - not previously  included in government figures - the 1995/96 total of &#163;1.22bn compares with &#163;717m the year before. The figures are calculated by multiplying by 32 the value of an erroneous claim to  represent the average time it would have continued if undetected.  <p>  <p>Meanwhile, it emerged that three weeks after closure of the Benefits Agency's free telephone lines  offering advice to claimants the agency's emergency out-of-hours service is under threat.  <p>  <p>Although the agency insisted that no decision had been taken, social workers believe existing  arrangements will cease in the autumn, leaving them to deal with the destitute. An agency office on  Merseyside has already written to social services, saying: "The service will be withdrawn in October.  The decision has been taken at national level, so all out-of-hours services throughout the country are  to be withdrawn."  <p>  <p>Benefits officers are on call at night, at weekends and on public holidays to consider help for  people who have no money. There is an out-of-hours office in south London. The service is under review  as the agency tries to meet ministers' demands that it cut its running costs by at least a quarter  over three years.  <p>  <p>A spokeswoman said social services departments were braced for the worst. They feared a steep  increase in their workload as social workers were called out to assist penniless people.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
