 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - A Florida jury awards $750,000 damages to a couple who sued  Brown & Williamson, a subsidiary of the British tobacco giant BAT </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Florida jury awards $750,000 damages to a couple who sued BAT subsidiary </b><br><br><br><b><h2>10 August 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Tobacco firm  loses cancer suit  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Mark Tran</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>The beleaguered tobacco industry last night suffered a legal setback when a Florida jury awarded  damages to a couple who sued Brown & Williamson, an American subsidiary of BAT, the British tobacco  giant.  <p>  <p>The only previous occassion on which a court ordered a tobacco company to pay up in a liability  suit occurred in 1988 in the Cippollone case. But that $400,000 (&#163;265,000) award was overturned  on appeal and the suit was dropped in 1992. The Florida case will almost certainly go to an appeals court. In at  least 19 liability suits, the industry has not yet had to pay a penny in damages.  <p>  <p>Word of the verdict sent shares of Philip Morris and RJR Nabisco down sharply. "This is a severe  blow to the industry," said Allan Kaplan, a tobacco analyst with Merrill Lynch. "We knew that when you  keep running cases, some jury is going to vote in favour of the plaintiff." The six-member jury in  Jacksonville ruled in favour of Grady Carter, aged 66, of Orange Park, Florida, awarding him $500,000,  and his wife, Millie, $250,000 in damages. The case, which was brought against American Tobacco, a  unit of Brown & Williamson, alleged that Mr Grady contracted lung cancer from smoking and that he was  misled by advertising into thinking that smoking was safe.  <p>  <p>The jury deliberated for nine-and-a-half hours over two days. The foreman, Samuel Gaskins, said  that the panel reviewed medical articles and technical documents, including material from Brown &  Williamson.  <p>  <p>Mr Carter, a retired air traffic controller, said: "Somebody needed to take these people on. A lot  of people are dying because of lung cancer." Brown & Williamson had argued that Mr Carter was aware of  the dangers but continued to smoke until he became ill in 1991. "He continued smoking Lucky Strikes  because he liked them," said tobacco company lawyer Bruce Sheffler, adding that Mr Carter only stopped  when he started coughing up blood. The tobacco industry is besieged by lawsuits. Several states are  demanding billions of dollars in compensation for health costs incurred by tobacco-related illness.  The Florida case was the first of a barrage of similar cases scheduled for this and next year in  Jacksonville. Mr Carter's attorney, Norwood Wilner, represents 60 clients with suits against tobacco  companies.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
