 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Belgium buries the two eight-year-old victims of a paedophile  gang with the ceremony of a state funeral </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Belgium buries the two eight-year-old victims of a paedophile gang </b><br><br><br><b><h2>19 August 1996</h2></b><br><h2>House of horrors stuns Belgium</h2><h3>Police  search for children's bodies amid fears of international sex ring </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Stephen Bates</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>A story of almost unimaginable horror was unfolding in Belgium yesterday as police searched for the  bodies of missing children at properties owned by a Belgian builder, who has admitted that two girls,  aged eight, starved to death while locked up at his home as he served a prison sentence last winter.  <p>  <p>With rumours of an international paedophile ring circulating, Belgian police have found three  bodies in the last 48 hours - the two missing eight-year-olds and an unnamed accomplice of the  builder.  <p>  <p>The arrested man, Marc Dutroux, aged 39, a convicted rapist, has been charged with abduction and  illegal kidnapping and is also likely to face murder charges.  <p>  <p>Discovery of the bodies of the two eight-year-olds brought to seven the number of dead girls found  at different locations after a series of disappearances dating back to 1989.  <p>  <p>Fears are growing for six other children, abducted or missing in recent years.  <p>  <p>Police yesterday said they were keeping an open mind about spreading their inquiries  internationally, including to Britain, in search of an organised kidnapping conspiracy by paedophiles.  <p>  <p>Michel Bourlet, the prosecuting magistrate, told a press conference yesterday that Mr Dutroux and  some of the five other people arrested had admitted kidnapping two teenage girls, Ann Marchal, aged  19, and Eefje Lambreks, aged 17, near Ostend last August.  <p>  <p>"Finding these girls is now the priority," Mr Bourlet said.  <p>  <p>Two other girls were found alive last Thursday, imprisoned in a tiny basement room at Mr Dutroux's  home in a village outside the southern Belgian city of Charleroi.  <p>  <p>Both had been sexually assaulted.  <p>  <p>Mr Dutroux allegedly told police: "I am going to give you two girls," and led them to a basement  where Laetitia Delheze, aged 14, who was kidnapped on 9 August, and Sabine Dardenne, 12, who  disappeared nearly three months ago, were locked in the room disguised behind a wall shielded by a  metal cupboard.  <p>  <p>Sabine, who endured 10 weeks in the room, which had bunks, books, a television and kitchen  equipment, was said to have wept and told her new companion, Laetitia: "I will never see my family  again." The crime has unnerving parallels with the case of Frederick West, the Gloucester builder, and  his wife Rosemary, who imprisoned and killed at least 12 young women. The police have brought in  mechanical diggers and pneumatic drills to dismantle Mr Dutroux's house in the village of Marcinelle  and 11 other homes he is believed to have owned.  <p>  <p>Mr Dutroux was sentenced to 13.5 years imprisonment in 1989 for the rape and abduction of  teenagers and the rape of a woman, aged 50. He was released from prison in 1992 after serving just  four years.  <p>  <p>His second wife, Michele Martin, a former teacher, has also been arrested, as has Michel Lelievre,  a lodger at their home; a Brussels estate agent named Jean-Michel Nihoul; and two others whose names  have not been released, one of whom is believed to be Greek.  <p>  <p>Mr Nihoul allegedly told police that Mr Dutroux had spoken of building cages to keep young girls  in.  <p>  <p>The chief investigator, Marcel Guissard, told the Guardian: "We have not ruled out an inquiry into  possible international paedophile links. We have not yet consulted other police forces, but may do  so." Ms Martin, aged 36, is protesting her innocence. The couple, who have been married for nearly  eight years, have a son aged three and a daughter aged eight months. Mr Dutroux also has a son, aged  12, by his first wife.  <p>  <p>Yesterday, police in Neufchateau, where the inquiry is centred, admitted they had searched the  house at Marcinelle several times over the last year without finding the hidden room. If they had  found it when they first visited the house a year ago, it seems certain that Julie Lejeune and Melissa  Russo would be alive.  <p>  <p>Mr Dutroux was imprisoned from last December to February this year on a charge of theft with  violence.  <p>  <p>Mr Guissard said: "The two little girls effectively starved to death. According to Dutroux's  statement he returned from prison to find one still alive. He saw her moving and tried to revive her  but it was too late." He claimed to have left money with associates so the children could be fed. The  disappearance of the two girls, while they were playing outside their homes in June 1995, caused an  immense search and widespread public anxiety in Belgium. Their pictures and descriptions were soon in  almost every shop window, but they appeared to have vanished until their bodies were dug up in Mr  Dutroux's back garden at the weekend.  <p>  <p>The rescued girls have told police that Mr Dutroux threatened that if they called out, they would  be dealt with by his associates "who are much more nasty than I am". The two children were silent when  the police broke in to rescue them.  <p>  <p>Mr Dutroux was traced after an eyewitness saw a van near the spot where Laetitia Delheze was  abducted as she walked home from a swimming pool and was able to recall the number plate.  <p>  <p>Mr Dutroux, who accompanied police during their search of his home on Saturday, was flown out by  helicopter to avoid a confrontation with angry crowds who besieged his house and the court at  Neufchateau where those arrested are being interrogated.  <p>  <p>Protesters have demanded the death penalty for Mr Dutroux and his wife, which even in Belgium's  current frenzied climate remains unlikely. Although the country still has the death penalty, it has  not been used since the execution of several hundred Nazi collaborators at the end of the second world  war.  <p>  <p>The father of Melissa Russo last night accused the authorities of not doing enough to find the two  girls. "It is very hard to bear that these children were alive for nine months and they could have  been saved," Gino Russo said. The police are coming under pressure for bungling the investigation, but  last night there were signs that the affair was also being laid at the door of senior politicians. A  recent law allows paedophiles early release, providing they seek therapy, but this is voluntary and  there are insufficient places for all to be treated.  <p>  <p>The families through their lawyer accused the government of paroling Mr Dutroux too early, and said  police had refused to let them accompany the original search of his home. If they had done so, the  relatives said, the children might have heard their voices and called out.  <p>  <p>  <p>    <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
