 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Rapist cross-examined his victim for six days after opting to defend himself </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Rapist cross-examined his victim for six days after opting to defend himself </b><br><br><br><b><h2>23 August 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Rape victim challenges law</h2><h3> Attacker  with long record of violence subjected victim to six gruelling days of cross examination  </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Hannah Pool</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>The victim of a rapist forced to endure six days of his cross-examination about his attacks in  court after he opted to defend himself, last night led calls for changes in the law to prevent other  women suffering a similar ordeal.  <p>  <p>Ralston Edwards, aged 42, was found guilty at the Old Bailey yesterday on two counts of rape.  Police observers said he had appeared to gain gratification when questioning the 34-year-old woman  during his trial. He has a long record of rape and violence to women.  <p>  <p>His victim, who has two children and is under 5ft tall, joined lawyers, court workers, police and  women's groups in calling on the Government to change the law which allowed Edwards to humiliate her.  A Home Office spokesman said: "The Government is concerned to ensure that victims of these hideous  crimes are adequately protected and we will be giving further consideration to the issues raised by  this case."  <p>  <p>Police officers last night praised the victim. On one occasion she had run from the courtroom,  physically sick, and yesterday left the Old Bailey in tears. She now depends on sleeping tablets and  valium.  <p>  <p>"I was raped once by Edwards and again by the British justice system," she is reported as saying in  this morning's Daily Mail. "To male politicians, I would urge them to swiftly change the law with  regard to rape victims. For God's sake and for women's sake may this never happen again." Edwards, of  Catford, south-east London, was found not guilty on two other charges of raping her over a 16-hour  period. He will be sentenced next month after psychiatric reports. Judge Ann Goddard, describing him  as dangerous, told him she was considering a life sentence. The jury of seven men and five women,  deliberated for five hours.  <p>  <p>Police revealed he was once acquitted of rape after defending himself. Edwards was jailed for three  years for breaking into a young woman's flat and raping her in front of her 16-month-old baby in 1984.  <p>  <p>He was jailed for three years in 1987 for causing his common law wife grievous bodily harm, and he  was jailed for four years in 1991, reduced to three, for two separate attacks on women.  <p>  <p>Detective Sergeant Milne Davidson, who led the investigation, supported calls for a change in the  law. He said after the case: '"He enjoyed every minute of it - reliving it all in detail. No doubt he  was getting some kind of sexual gratification and pleasure from it. He is very cunning and into  domination."  <p>  <p>After Edwards exercised his right to defend himself, Judge Goddard gave him considerable leeway to  avoid giving him grounds for appeal. She told the jury: "The rules have been somewhat flexible during  the case." He forced his victim to relive her rape in minute detail, but she tried to answer every  question. She once said: "I don't think you appreciate the terror you are putting me through."  <p>  <p>Some of Edwards's questions verged on the bizarre. He had given her a milkshake at his home and  wanted to know what flavour it was. "What were the colour of bricks in the alley you say I took you  to?" he asked. The woman says she has now moved "a very long way" from the scene of the attack.  <p>  <p>After the verdicts, Edwards requested a solicitor and barrister for his sentencing.  <p>  <p>The Old Bailey had heard the victim was standing at a bus stop in Catford in December 1995 when  Edwards approached her for a cigarette. She was moving property from the house she had shared with her  alcoholic husband to her boyfriend's.  <p>  <p>Edwards bundled her into an alleyway when she got off the bus, and forced her to go to his home  which had neither heat nor light. He claimed she had gone willingly and suggested she had had sex in  the hour between leaving his house and reporting the rape.  <p>  <p>His victim told the jury that in the alley, as he kissed her and his hands were all over her, she  was frightened that if she screamed he might become violent.  <p>  <p>At his filthy home, Edwards showed no intention of letting her leave. "He wanted to keep me. I  don't know how, but he really wanted to keep me." She added: "I was afraid of what was going to  happen. It was obvious that something was going to happen. I had almost given up the fight. Was I  going to live or was I going to die? He started pulling at my clothes and it was obvious I was going  to be raped.  <p>  <p>"I was constantly the whole time pleading with him that I had to go, that I had children. I tried  to reason with him like a human being but he didn't seem to care. It was as though my life was  irrelevant. It was as though I was his property."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
