 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Liam Gallagher pulls out of Oasis US tour to go househunting with fianc&#233;e </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Liam Gallagher pulls out of Oasis US tour to go househunting with fianc&#233;e </b><br><br><br><b><h2>30 August 1996</h2></b><br><h2>'This is  Spinal Tap' and we can't get enough of it   </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Caroline Sullivan</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Liam Gallagher has probably never seen 'This Is Spinal Tap', being too busy living the rock star life  to watch a movie parodying it, but if he had he'd probably recognise himself in the Nigel Tufnel  character. Tufnel is temperamental and impetuous, prone to mid-show walk-offs and rows with the  long-suffering guitarist. Liam may not have stooped to emulating Tufnel's Lycra leggings - yet - but  otherwise, it's a clear case of life imitating art.  <p>  <p>Gallagher's public behaviour has been spoiled, brattish and stupid ever since Oasis came along  three years ago, and we adore every ill-judged second of it. With the exception of Michael Jackson,  he's the best pop soap opera in the last 15 years, invariably leaping without looking and damn the  consequences.  <p>  <p>His refusal to accompany the rest of the group to America on Monday because he wanted to buy a  house was Liam at his Liamest. "I can't go around looking for a house while I'm playing for silly  fucking Yanks," he scowled through his hideous new beard. The first date, a 17,500-seater in Chicago,  went ahead without him, though a fan complained on TV, "I feel I'm being cheated if I don't see Liam  sing; there's no point without him." (Yep, they love him there despite his contempt toward Americans.  A source at Epic Records in New York said, "Maybe people here just like the abuse. At least he has a  personality.") Everything Gallagher does reinforces his reputation as a heat-seeking missile. From the  furious quarrels with Noel (one was clandestinely recorded and released as a most excellent single,  Wibbling Rivalry) to the mandatory affair-with-sexy actress to the drug abuse, he's doing it all by  the rock star script. Yet Liam is too ingenuous to misbehave for its PR effect; he is just following  his instincts. And, fortunately, those instincts are the worst.  <p>  <p>'Fortunately' because everything he does is such compulsive viewing. Before Gallagher, rock excess  had been out of fashion for many years. The days when Keith Moon could drive his Rolls-Royce into a  swimming pool with impunity had been succeeded, thanks to Live Aid, by a soberer mind-set. It's been  an REM-ish world since, stuffed with musos who get the job done, then go home. Humbug. No wonder we're  so thrilled by the odd incidence of colourful behaviour, like Jarvis Cocker's clash with Jacko. Liam,  bless his self-destructive soul, is colourful every minute of the day. He seems to have absolutely no  sense of enough being enough, and we love, love, love it. That doesn't mean he's destined for the  early demise of pop stars who live too much. His relationship with Noel, tempestuous though it is,  seems to exert a steadying influence. Northern to the marrow, he places great store in family ties,  and he and Noel will probably plod into old age together. As for leaving Oasis - he's not that silly.  He knows what happened when Sid Vicious went solo.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
