 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - The Prince and Princess of Wales divorce</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>The Prince and Princess of Wales divorce</b><br><br><br><b><h2>29 August 1996</h2></b><br><h2>So why did the Princess wear the rings?   </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Sally Weale</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>With this ring I thee wed, with my body I thee worship, and with all my worldly goods I thee endow.  <p>  <p>She may have been stripped of her title, but yesterday, as an anonymous clerk in the bowels of Somerset House rubber-stamped the divorce of the century, Diana, Princess of Wales, made it plain that she and her diamonds are not to be parted.  <p>  <p>As she made her first public appearance as a divorced woman at the headquarters of the English National Ballet, all eyes fell to her left hand, on which she wore the bulky sapphire and diamond engagement ring which launched the Wales's ill-fated union - and a million cheap Ratner's copies besides. Tucked beside it, for those with sharp eyes, was the plain band of Welsh gold that Charles slipped on to her finger in St Paul's. In 15 years of public squabbling and private despair, the dazzling blue and white cluster, purchased for &#163;28,500 by Charles as bridegroom-to-be from Garrard, has endured. It was there at the beginning, in the awkwardly posed engagement pictures; it was on the mugs and the posters; it was there on the foreign tours; it was probably there in the operating theatre, tucked away under latex gloves, in breach of hospital hygiene regulations. But why, on the day the marriage finally ended, did she decide to wear it? For dyed in the wool feminists, the ring has always been the symbol of the oppression of marriage, to be cast off with a triumphant flourish. But with one in three marriages now ending in divorce, the ring has lost much of its historic symbolism.  <p>  <p>Diana's decision to wear hers may be little more than a final gesture of girlish defiance. It's a bloody nice ring, why shouldn't she wear it?   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
