 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Sole female editor Sue Douglas resigns from the Sunday Express </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Sole female editor Sue Douglas resigns from the Sunday Express </b><br><br><br><b><h2>4 September 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Express discards sole female editor  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Maggie Brown</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Sue Douglas, the only female editor of a national newspaper, resigned yesterday from her &#163;175,000 a year post at the helm of the Sunday Express after eight tumultuous months.  <p>  <p>Insiders said she had paid the price for imposing revolution rather than evolution on the title, scaring middle-aged male readers away with provocative columnists and misjudged headlines.  <p>  <p>Her regime will be remembered for the shock of a front page splash last April, 'A bunch of shits', claiming to quote John Major on European leaders during a summit meeting - rather than for the new sports section and magazine with which she tried to pep up the paper and appeal to younger readers.  <p>  <p>She alienated many staff by her high-handed 'Queen of Sheba' behaviour and willingness to sack long-serving staffers: one, Graham Jones, complained of being discarded like a toffee wrapper, and took her to an industrial tribunal. It found she had hired and fired with complete disregard to good employment practice. "The atmosphere has been toxic," one staff member said yesterday.  <p>  <p>The former deputy editor of the Sunday Times, aged 39, was toppled after returning from holiday in Scotland and was yesterday negotiating a pay-off expected to approach &#163;400,000. Those who had spoken to her report that she was resentful at the way her hard work was being downplayed. She also dismissed suggestions that she may wish to move into the Channel 5 or television arm of MAI, the parent company.  <p>  <p>The Daily and Sunday Express, both selling about 1.2 million copies and urgently seeking readers after 25 years of decline, are being merged into a single editorial team, under Richard Addis, editor of the Daily Express. About 85 jobs, equivalent to the staff of the Sunday paper, are being axed, saving about &#163;4m.  <p>  <p>The weak sister paper, the tabloid Daily Star, is unaffected by the changes. Seven-day operations are common in the United States and some European countries and have been flirted with at the Daily and Sunday Telegraph and the Independent and Independent on Sunday. But they have yet to prove workable in Britain where Sunday papers have personalities of their own. Sir David English, chairman of Associated Newspapers, whose Daily Mail and Mail on Sunday dominate the middle market in which Express titles have to sell, said: "They will be going against the newspaper culture of this country."  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
