 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Style Wars Between Armani And Versace</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Style wars between Armani and Versace</b><br><br><br><b><h2>18 September 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Style: Off the Cuff  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Susannah Frankel</b><br><br><br>      <p>  <p><b>The importance of being early</b>  <p>  <p>Slapped wrists all round in the Guardian fashion department for daring to suggest that Gianni Versace has overtaken Giorgio Armani to become Hollywood's favourite designer. Just to prove how wrong we are, a seriously disgruntled press officer faxed a list of celebrities who attended the Emporio Armani shop opening in New York last week, which includes the star-spangled likes of Auermann Nadja, Campbell Naomi, Ryder Winona, Dylan Bob, Lee Spike, Lovett Lyle, etc, etc. Said list also made it clear that we are not the only people with whom Mr Armani has taken issue. A couple of the celebrities mentioned obviously didn't realise just how important such an occasion might be. Or is 'Fishburne Laurence (late)' and 'Jones Quincy (late)' just some weird kind of fashion code?  <p>  <p><b>For you...</b>  <p>  <p>ESPA, the dreamy beauty product range designed to "care for the face, body and mind", has a special offer for Guardian readers. The first 100 who call and confirm an appointment for an ESPA Express Facial or Body Treatment at Liberty's Beauty Room (Regent St, London W1), between 23 and 28 September, will receive a special discounted booking fee of &#163;10 (redeemable against purchase) plus a complimentary ESPA Soothing Massage Oil (worth &#163;11.95). To book, tel 0171 734 1234 and ask for the ESPA counter.  <p>  <p><b>and you</b>  <p>  <p>Also at Liberty, Face Stockholm, a new cosmetic line that "recognises, honours and embraces the uniqueness and integrity of each customer" (blimey, slap with integrity), is offering a free lip gloss to the first 100 people who visit the counter on Monday 30 September. "The lip gloss can be used alone or on top of lipstick for high-shine, dramatic lips," apparently. Like Liz Hurley's!  <p>  <p><b>Band on the run</b>  <p>  <p>Footballers have always had more than their fair share of bad hair days (bad hair lives). Think Chris Waddle - long at the back, short at the front and bleached. Or Terry McDermott (Ronald McDonald looks positively coiffed by comparison). Or Gazza, all platinum blond... But, after a history of bad hair on the pitch, Liverpool's Patrik Berger has come up with a thoroughly stylish solution to keep his tresses at bay. The Alice band! If he's brave enough to wear one, who are we to criticise?  <p>  <p><b>Now showing</b>  <p>  <p>Fashion bunnies the world over will be delighted to know that throughout London Fashion Week, they can tap into the Vogue internet site (Vogue Fashion Daily) and view twice-daily catwalk reports. The service begins on Monday 23 September, carrying show previews, and from Wednesday to Sunday, reports at 1pm and 6pm will bring the website's global audience an up-to-the-minute account of the best of the shows. Vogue Fashion Daily <A HREF="http://www.">http://www. vogue.co.uk</A>  <p>  <p><b>Happy birthday, Knickerbox</b>  <p>  <p>This month, Knickerbox is 10 years old. Although M&S still wins hands down in the most-enormous-selection-of-reasonably-priced-underwear-known-to-man stakes, the younger chain does offer a more manageable alternative for those looking for a comprehensive selection of directional smalls.   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><