 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Prince Charles criticises "unnatural practices" in farming</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Prince Charles criticises "unnatural practices" in farming</b><br><br><br><b><h2>20 September 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Prince hits at farming's "unnatural" methods  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Paul Brown</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Prince Charles hit out at "unnatural practices" in farming yesterday and said the BSE crisis was the result of catastrophic experiments in treating animals like machines.  <p>  <p>In an indictment of British farming policy and its results in destruction of wildlife, he suggested that mad cow disease was the result of man disturbing the balance of nature. "Perhaps BSE will come to be seen as one example, albeit a very expensive and damaging one, of how nature hits back when we violate her laws."  <p>  <p>He also said the decline in male fertility across Europe might be linked to diet, and vital minerals in fruit and vegetables had been lost because of intensive farming.  <p>  <p>In the speech last night to the organic farming organisation, the Soil Association, on its 50th anniversary, he pulled no punches in condemning current agricultural practices and the failure of the Government to give organic farming a fair chance to compete.  <p>  <p>He took pains to defend individual farmers who had been locked into intensive production because of polices which stemmed from the food shortages of the last war and the need for self sufficiency. The prince, who practises organic farming at his Highgrove estate, said the effect of intensive farming on animals was often horrifying. "We must recognise that for the last 50 years we have given our farmers a remarkably narrow set of goals, and accompanying incentives to help them get there: economic performance without environmental accountability; maximum production without consideration of food quality and health; intensification without regard for animal welfare; specialisation without the consideration of the maintenance of biological and cultural diversity. The signals we sent said we wanted cheap food and plenty of it. We can hardly blame the farmers now for their outstanding success in achieving these goals."  <p>  <p>Urgent reform of the Common Agricultural Policy was needed to change the farmers' role. Looking after the countryside as a service to society as a whole had to be recognised in farmers' pay.  <p>  <p>He revealed that he had arranged two seminars at Sandringham to discuss future farming policy. These had included European farmers who also wanted reform. He said a seminar between farmers and environmentalists in Brussels next month, to be attended by EU Commissioners, was a further step towards that reform.  <p>  <p>He was not interested in returning to the past, but learning from it. Highgrove, which had been farmed organically for 11 years, was profitable, with premium prices obtained for produce.  <p>  <p>He criticised the Ministry of Agriculture for its failure to encourage other farms to convert to organic production, saying that the financial incentives to do so were less than of any other country in Europe.  <p>  <p>The way a country grew its food was a model of its society: "If the way in which people farm is grasping, looks only to the short-term, and is indifferent to the effects of what is being done to the generations that will follow, then that is what their society will be like too."   <p>  <p><b>Soil matters</b>  <p>  <p>Britain has 800 organic farms, a total of 120,400 acres - less than one per cent of the land farmed.  <p>  <p>Germany and Denmark expect to have 10 per cent organic farms by 2000. Dairy cows which once lived 20 years now produce their own body weight of milk every month and "milk themselves to death in seven years", Prince Charles said.  <p>  <p>More than 50 per cent of Britons would buy organic food if it were available, according to MORI polls.  <p>  <p>The UK has the lowest level of incentive payments to farm organically in Europe.  <p>  <p>The cost of BSE is so far estimated at &#163;1.4bn.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
