 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Claudia Schiffer retires at  26</TITLE></HEAD> <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000"  alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea"> <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br>
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Claudia Schiffer retires  at 26</b><br><br><br><b><h2>27 September 1996</h2></b><br><h2>People said Claudia Schiffer was too sweet for the Nineties, so what's she doing with a man like Abel Ferrara?  </h2>
 <br>By 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Brian Logan</b><br><br>      <p> <p>What is the most innocent and beautiful woman on the catwalk doing with  the seediest, low-down renegade in American cinema? Having announced her  retirement from modelling, Claudia Schiffer is making her first movie, with the  maestro of the Lower East Side demi-monde, Abel Ferrara. It's a bizarre coupling.  <p> <p>And what of the rumour - not surprising given the Ferrara canon - that she  gets raped in her first scene? "We're not authorised to comment," comments  Schiffer's agency, Metropolitan, in New York. Excuse me? Is Claudia Schiffer, the  vegetarian, teetotal, non-smoking image of perfection to be sullied by amoral  Ferrara? Over to Steven Zeller, publicist for the film, The Blackout. He says: "I  can't remember. I think if Claudia Schiffer got raped, I would remember." The  rumour is groundless. <p> <p>'The Blackout', which has just finished shooting in  Miami, is Ferrara's first venture since his almost-excellent 1930s gangster  flick, 'The Funeral', made a killing at the Venice Film Festival. His has been a  distinctive, rather than distinguished, career, in a long tradition of  non-mainstream New York film-makers. His 1979 debut 'Driller Killer' - in which  an artist, irked by noisy neighbours, drills everyone to death - is the prototype  video nasty. His most renowned feature, 'Bad Lieutenant', charts miserable  moments in the life of a bent cop who wallows in drugs 'n' sleaze until  stimulated to redemption by the rape of a 'beautiful young nun'. He followed that  with 'Dangerous Game', a grim film- within-a-film, 'like "Who's Afraid Of  Virginia Woolf' on acid". <p> <p>Not unlike Scorsese, he dwells on religion,  salvation and self-destruction; his movies exploit, shock and - sometimes -  subvert. In his time, Ferrara has outraged the tabloids, the moral majority and  the liberal establishment. 'Driller Killer' had a special screening in the House  of Commons. He doesn't seem to care. On his partnership with actor Christopher  Walken he once told the Guardian: "We're like Fassbinder. Just get the cash, get  the chicks and shoot it over the weekend, like a porn movie." Schiffer can be  naughty - "I ate a whole bar of chocolate!" - but usually she is "very romantic.  I like candle-lit dinners and curling up at home and watching movies on the  television." Movies like Ferrara's 'Ms 45', in which a deaf-mute rape victim  wreaks vengeance on the male world? It seems unlikely. Perhaps Ferrara identified  a gritty Schiffer alter-ego through reading 'Memories', her photo-laden  autobiography ("I didn't write it, but I like it"): According to the blurb: "Her  life is a reflection of the inner integrity that flows from her wholeness,  harmony and radiance." Schiffer - or Choufleur, as some unimpressed photographers  once dubbed her - has until now remained an unexploded German bombshell. In 1992,  she launched a &#163;17m lawsuit against a paparazzo who snapped her starkers  during a quick change; it jeopardised, she protested, her &#163;4.5m Revlon  contract. Her two-year engagement to magician David Copperfield lent polish to  the image; subsequent suggestions that it was an affair of convenience to bolster  her fame in the States and his in Europe left her name untarnished. So what  possessed her to throw in her lot - and, at &#163;4,784 per minute on the  catwalk, it's a lot - with Abel Ferrara? Claudia has put herself on the chopping  block. Is this any time to remind her that the most recent Ferrara hero, the  Italian avenger Ray Temple, wielded a sharp axe? Mark Damon, the MD in MDP  Worldwide, producers of the movie, explains: "Abel was saying he'd like to use a  very-well known actress, or a very famous model who wanted to act. I thought  Claudia might be interested. She'd received over 100 offers before and turned  them all down; but she was fascinated with this script, and with the prospect of  working with a talented director like Ferrara." Schiffer's part is that of a Soho  art dealer and girlfriend of Matthew Modine's drug 'n' booze junkie who's been  chronically affected by Beatrice Dalle and Dennis Hopper, and who has 'entered  the dark side'. That's Hollywood-ese for a baby-murdering, beer-swillingly bad  hangover. Her role, according to Damon, is very meaty, which may refer to the  scene in which her loved one walks into the sea telling Claudia that he's  murdered his ex. As an untrained actress, could she cope? "She was excellent,"  says Damon. "In her first scene, she was a little tense and nervous, and she  wasn't doing too well. So Abel stopped the shoot, they went off for three hours  and they improvised. Abel discovered that, as soon as she improvised, she became  natural and real." The best and most gruelling scene in Ferrara's 'Dangerous  Game' features Madonna improvising an actress improvising a scene in a movie.  Ferrara enjoys that kind of game. "I think," says Damon, "he's the best director  around for actors today." In today's Hollywood, there's no shortage of MTAs -  Models Turned Actressses. Many model agencies have established special divisions  and Equity, the actors' union, has a distinct category, Models/Temporary  Membership, for models taking to the stage or the screen. "Modelling," says Sarah  Doukas, head honcho at London agency Storm, "has gone extremely high-profile. If  you put Kate Moss in a film, the box office would turn serious money, because  there's a huge interest in her." But is there a logical progression from  modelling to acting? Saffron Burrows, model and star of Dennis Potter's Karaoke  and Cold Lazarus, doesn't think so. She says: "Modelling is the antithesis of  acting. It can be like an out-of-body experience: you're constantly aware of your  own body language, of everything you're projecting, to an extent that's very  unhealthy. If you do it for too long, it's hard to lose yourself in a character."  <p> <p>Schiffer has aspired to the screen for some time. "I look at scripts  periodically and would like to find the right role but I have to study and learn  more about acting," she said three years ago. <p> <p>Ferrara's opinions on acting  are legendary. Of his usual principals, Harvey Keitel and Walken, he claims: "I  just let 'em go. I just make sure they're in focus." As for his relationship with  actors: "All they care about in Hollywood is sympathy for the character. I never  did understand that concept. My guys ain't asking for sympathy." When all else  fails, glamour counts in the US. Ferrara wants it, and doesn't care where he  finds it, as his casting of Madonna demonstrates. <p> <p>He seems to relish  demystifying and humbling those who seem untouchable. So why did Schiffer choose  'The Blackout'? She may be grabbing at gravitas. It has been argued that if his  films had subtitles, Ferrara would be called an auteur. <p> <p>And she must have  been aware her catwalk appeal was waning. "I don't want to be nasty," said  Jean-Paul Gaultier unconvincingly last year, "but she's got no personality."  Popularity polls across Europe identified her as fake and manufactured. The  perception, after she retired last week at 26, is that her look is irredeemably  dated. <p> <p>So can the pure public face of Schiffer survive now she's to appear  in a seamy Ferrara flick? Those in the know say yes. For while Dalle, as Matty's  other lover, has passionate sex in the back of a car, and aborts her baby -  commonplace by Ferrara standards, "Claudia stays sweet and innocent," says Mark  Damon. <p> <p>"Modine has three relationships in this movie; Claudia's is the  most likely to succeed, because she's sweet and supportive. She's a giving person  who has a vulnerability that comes out on screen." Hollywood is a place of  miracles. As Sixties waif Twiggy announced on the very day in 1970 when she quit  the catwalk to become an actor: "I couldn't do a big dramatic acting part, but  I'm willing to try anything that's nice." <p> <p> <p> <p> <br><br><center><TABLE  border=0><tr> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400  border=0><tr> <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A  HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=center valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=right valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td> </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
