 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Government figures show Camelot paid out less than 15% of awards to causes>  </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Government figures show Camelot paid out less than 15 per cent of awards to causes</b><br><br><br><b><h2>21 September 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Lottery cash delays boost Treasury</h2><h3>More than £2bn has been allocated to lottery good causes but only £374m has been paid out</h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Maev Kennedy</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Less than 15 per cent of almost &#163;2.5bn available to the five lottery good causes has actually been paid out, according to government figures.  <p>  <p>Figures disclosed by the Heritage Minister Iain Sproat to the former Tory prime minister Sir Edward Heath reveal that although more than &#163;2bn has been allocated in grants, in the fields of arts, sports, heritage, millennium and charities, just over &#163;317m has been paid out. That figure has risen, in the round of grants over the last few weeks, to &#163;374m.  <p>  <p>The undistributed money helps make the Government's finances look rosier. Although the money remains part of the good causes funds, and earning interest for them, for accountancy purposes the &#163;2bn is counted as part of the Government's wealth until it is paid out, and helps reduce the Public Sector Borrowing Requirement.  <p>  <p>A Department of National Heritage spokeswoman confirmed the figures yesterday, but said: "We expect the sum to reduce rapidly once a wide range of projects comes on stream." Mr Sproat insists that "the impression that little money has actually been paid out" is false.  <p>  <p>The lowest percentage paid out of the amounts awarded is the millennium grants, at three per cent, and the applicants to the heritage fund have done best, at 29 per cent paid out. The arts fund has paid out 17 per cent, the sports fund 21, and charities 23.  <p>  <p>Mr Sproat said 71 per cent of successful applicants had received at least part of their money, rising to 90 per cent in the charities sector. A spokeswoman for the Millennium Commission said that many of their projects were fairly large, and were subject to delays in detailed designs and planning permission. The money will also be paid out on a milestone basis, with some paid over as foundations of buildings go in, and more as the building work proceeds. Legal agreeements have been signed committing the fund to &#163;232m payments.  <p>  <p>A Heritage fund spokeswoman said they had paid out more than the other bodies because many grants were for acquisitions of objects, buildings or land at auction, while their fast-track procedure for urgent appeals had led to some being processed and agreed within two days.  <p>  <p>But thousands of projects are stalled waiting for the necessary partnership funding to match the grants, as the letter from Mr Sproat admits. The distributing bodies see lottery funding as a means of attracting other funds. "The award may be made before the entire partnership funding package is in place, although no money will be paid until the distributing body is satisfied that all conditions of the award have been met."  <p>  <p>Mr Sproat defends the figures, saying that successful applicants only get their money when they hand in the relevant invoices. "A long-term project will therefore only be drawing down funds in a number of instalments, and this will add to the impression that little money has actually been paid out."  <p>  <p>Sir Edward, MP for Old Bexley and Sidcup, sought the figures on behalf of Denis Vaughan, who lays claim to having invented the lottery, and has been critical of the way it has been set up, through his Lottery Promotion Company.  <p>  <p>Although all the lottery funds have relaxed the rules on partnership funding and found ways around the original strict rule on funding only capital schemes, many projects are having great difficulty finding the extra funding, particularly in poor areas, or where many different projects are competing.  <p>  <p>The chairman of English Heritage, Sir Jocelyn Stevens, has already attacked the heritage fund for failures, delays and restrictions.  <p>  <p>The art world expressed envy last week when the Wallace Collection in London applied for a &#163;7.5m grant with all its partnership funding in place, through a single &#163;2.5m donation.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
