 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Diarmuid O¼Neill shot dead in police raid on IRA arms cache in Hammersmith </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Diarmuid O'Neill shot dead in police raid on IRA arms cache in Hammersmith </b><br><br><br><b><h2>28 September 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Anti-terror police check on ETA after O'Neill death  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David Sharrock</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Scotland Yard and Spanish anti-terrorist police have launched a new investigation into links between the IRA and ETA because of the relationship between Diarmuid O'Neill, the IRA suspect shot dead by police in west London, and a woman from the Basque country.  <p>  <p>The pro-ETA newspaper Egin, which wants an independent Basque country, this week published a death notice for O'Neill, whose killing is the subject of a police inquiry. Accompanied by an Irish tricolour, it read: "Ginger. Killed by the English police 23 September. From all your friends in Amorebieta." Amorebieta is a small industrial town close to Bilbao, where O'Neill's girlfriend Karmele Ereno lives.  <p>  <p>A relative yesterday denied reports that Ms Ereno was still living in London. Neighbours of her family in Spain said the family had no known links with ETA or its political wing Herri Batasuna. But they revealed that O'Neill spent time in the Basque Country with Ms Ereno this summer.  <p>  <p>Police sources in Madrid said the Comisaria General de Informacion - the anti-terrorist branch of the national police force - has been contacted in the past few days by Scotland Yard about Ms Ereno. It is likely that they will be looking for her to question her about her relationship with O'Neill. According to neighbours in Amorebieta, Ms Ereno, aged 27, travelled to London three years ago to live and learn English. O'Neill had made several visits to the area in the past few years and became a familiar figure. British and Spanish police have worked together before in tracing links between ETA and the IRA, which are believed to have first been established in 1972.  <p>  <p>In London, O'Neill's parents described him last night as an "unselfish and loving son". In a prepared statement, released several hours after their youngest son Shane was released from custody in Paddington Green police station, Eoghan and Theresa O'Neill claimed the police had taken the law into their own hands.  <p>  <p>Mr and Mrs O'Neill, who live in County Cork, returned to London after the pre-dawn police and MI5 raids in London and Sussex in the early hours of Monday. "We are relieved that our youngest son, Shane, has been released from custody and that we have him with us safely," their statement read. "Diarmuid was never arrested; he can never be tried, nor can he be acquitted or convicted other than by the press who have not waited to have a full and proper picture before judging him. Instead, those who accused him took the law into their own hands and killed him."  <p>  <p>Four other IRA suspects arrested on Monday were last night still being interviewed by detectives. They will have to be charged or released by Monday morning.  <p>  <p>A delegation from the Police Complaints Authority yesterday inspected the room in Hammersmith where Diarmuid O'Neill was killed.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
