 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - New method of contraception  introduced</TITLE></HEAD> <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000"  alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea"> <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br>
<!--INFOLINE--><b>New method of  contraception introduced</b><br><br><br><b><h2>1 October  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Green light for rhythm method  </h2>
 <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Chris  Mihill</b><br><br>      <p> <p>A hitech form of the rhythm method of contraception which is said to be  95 per cent reliable goes on sale today, allowing women more accurately to judge  when it is safe to have sex without the risk of pregnancy. A pocket-sized monitor  lights up green when it is safe to make love without contraception, and red when  it is not. An amber light means the user must carry out a simple urine test to  determine if she is near ovulation. To use the Persona system, a woman presses a  button on the first day of her period. The method is said to be as reliable as  the condom when used properly. Only five to seven out of 100 women using it for a  year are expected to become pregnant. <p> <p>Rhythm methods are popular among  Catholics, it being the one method of birth control which is sanctioned by their  church. However, it has often been criticised as unreliable. <p> <p>Persona has  been tested in some 1,200 women in Britain, Ireland and Germany over the past two  years.The manufacturers, Unipath, who make home pregnancy and ovulation  test kits, say that the method should allow couples to make love without a  contraceptive on most days of the month. <p> <p>The system works by measuring two  hormones, E3G and LH, which tell when the fertile period begins and ends. On average each woman will have six to 10 fertile days a month when she is at  risk of pregnancy. <p> <p>The volunteers in the trial were aged 18 to 45 and in  established relationships. More than 3,200 questionnaires found that 95  per cent of women found Persona easy to use. Sandra Pickerton, aged 28,  said: "There are no drawbacks to it at all. You soon get used to looking at the  monitor every morning. If you don't remember, and you should have done a  test, there's a leeway of three hours. And if you forget you'll just get more red  lights - usually you get six to 10 a month. It's great to dispense with  condoms except when you need them, and to know when you're ovulating and when  you're about to have your period, so that mood swings and bodily changes fall  into place." <p> <p>However the cost of Persona may put off some potential users.  The monitor and initial starter pack will retail at &#163;49.95, and monthly  supplies of urine testing equipment will cost &#163;9.95. The Family Planning  Association welcomed the method, saying it would give couples more choice. <p>  <p>However, it is not recommended for women who are not in committed  relationships because it encourages them to stop using condoms, which protect  against sexually transmitted diseases including HIV. The pill is still the most  popular form of contraception, but women have been frightened by recent health  scares. <p> <p>"Many women still have needless fears about taking the pill," says  Ann Furedi, director of the Birth Control Trust. There is a lot of  interest in natural family planning." <p> <p> <p> <p> <br><br><center><TABLE  border=0><tr> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400  border=0><tr> <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A  HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=center valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=right valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td> </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
