 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Hamilton libel case against Guardian  collapses spectacularly </TITLE></HEAD> <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000"  link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea"> <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br>
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Hamilton libel case  against Guardian collapses spectacularly </b><br><br><br><b><h2>2 October  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Hamilton admits: 'I took money'</h2><h3>Disgraced former minister  confesses he took £10,000 and free holidays  </h2>
 <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David  Leigh</b><br><br>      <p> <p>Neil Hamilton, the disgraced former trade minister, last night  sensationally admitted for the first time that he took money from parliamentary  lobbyist Ian Greer. <p> <p>Mr Hamilton, MP for Tatton, also conceded he had told  deputy Prime Minister Michael Heseltine that he did not have a financial  relationship with Mr Greer. <p> <p>But in an extraordinary development last  night, he told the BBC he did not believe that taking the money constituted a  financial relationship. Mr Hamilton changed his story after his one-time friend  Mr Greer, who also dropped a libel action against the Guardian yesterday, had  confirmed earlier that he had twice paid Mr Hamilton for what he described as  "introductions". Mr Hamilton had given the assurance to Mr Heseltine in October  1994 after the Guardian had outlined how he had taken cash from Mr Greer and  Mohamed Al Fayed, owner of Harrods, in return for asking parliamentary questions.  Although conceding he took money from Mr Greer, also named in the Guardian story  two years ago, Mr Hamilton still denied taking the money from Mr Al Fayed. <p>  <p>Alan Rusbridger, the editor of the Guardian, said: "This climbdown is the  second astonishing U-turn Mr Hamilton has made in the space of 24 hours. "Most  people would understand this as meaning he has lied to Michael Heseltine. It is  difficult to see how he can stay on as an MP after this." Central to Mr  Hamilton's altered argument is a reliance on the semantics of what he denies is a  "financial relationship". <p> <p>In his statement, Mr Hamilton said: "When the  media were baying for my resignation in 1994, and besieging me whilst on a visit  to a school in my constituency, I had a fraught telephone conversation with the  President of the Board of Trade, Michael Heseltine. "He asked me if I had  a 'financial relationship' with Ian Greer. I responded I had not. It was my view  - then - and now - that the receipt of two payments many years ago did not  constitute 'a financial relationship' which implies some form of continuing  obligation." <p> <p>On BBC TV last night, Mr Hamilton revealed one of the  payments he disclosed last night was for &#163;6,000. The other was for  &#163;4,000. <p> <p>Mr Hamilton refused to answer repeated questions on whether  he had taken other payments in kind, other than a week-long stay at Mr Al Fayed's  Ritz, already revealed by the Guardian. He also admitted last night he had taken  another holiday at Mr Al Fayed's castle in Scotland. <p> <p>In his statement, Mr  Hamilton said: "The commissions placed me under no obligation whatever, either to  Ian Greer or his company. They were wholly unconnected to my position as an MP,  and similar payments are frequently made throughout industry to people in all  walks of life." <p> <p>But evidence in the possession of the Guardian shows that  Mr Hamilton went on to ask parliamentary questions and write letters to ministers  on behalf of the companies he had introduced to Mr Greer for the &#163;6,000 and  &#163;4,000 payments. <p> <p>One of the Greer payments was made in respect of one  of Mr Hamilton's constituents. That meant he was being paid extra for doing his  constituency business. <p> <p>After Mr Hamilton's admissions, the affair  continued to gather momentum. Labour's campaigns spokesman, Brian Wilson, said:  "The allegations are of a devastating order for the Tory party and the idea that  they can suppress them simply by getting rid of this court case will just not be  acceptable to Parliament or indeed the electorate." <p> <p>With Sir Gordon  Downey, the Parliamentary Commissioner for Standards, saying he was ready to  investigate, Mr Heseltine's office was indicating its reluctance to release a key  document which would prove Mr Hamilton had lied. Lord Nolan, who conducted the  original 'sleaze' inquiry which called for a tightening of MPs' standards  following the Guardian's investigations, said: "The continuing accusations and  counter-accusations are damaging the reputation of Parliament." <p> <p>Mr  Hamilton said he would not resign his Tatton seat: "In this country, a man is  innocent until proven guilty, except in the columns of the Guardian." <p> <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr> <td  align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG  border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=center valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=right valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td> </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
