 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Fred and Rosemary West's house demolished to deter souvenir hunters </TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Fred and Rosemary West's house demolished to deter souvenir hunters </b><br><br><br><b><h2>5 October 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Wests' house of horrors to bite the dust  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Duncan Campbell</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>The most notorious house in Britain is to be obliterated. On Monday morning, builders will begin a two-week operation to destroy the last remnants of 25 Cromwell Street in Gloucester, where Fred and Rosemary West buried their victims.  <p>  <p>As the dust settles, a company will start interviewing relatives of the Wests' victims and Cromwell Street neighbours about what should happen to the site. One suggestion is that it should become a memorial garden. But last night Caroline Owens, one of the victims of the Wests to escape with her life, said that she was strongly opposed to any kind of memorial at the site.  <p>  <p>"I'd like to see it knocked down so that no sign of it is left at all," said Ms Owens, who in 1972 was attacked and raped by the Wests, for whom she had worked briefly as a nanny. Her evidence was a key factor in the conviction of Mrs West for 10 murders at her trial in Winchester crown court last year. "I don't think a memorial garden is a good idea, as I don't think people would respect it," said Ms Owens, of Cinderford, Gloucestershire, who recently married.  <p>  <p>She added that she felt a plaque or memorial stone in Gloucester Cathedral would be more appropriate: "Somewhere peaceful, a nicer place to remember the girls."  <p>  <p>A spokesman for Gloucester city council said yesterday that the council had paid the West estate &#163;40,000 to purchase the house. As yet no decision had been made as to what would be done with the empty site, he said. One possibility is a car park. Neighbours complain that sightseers still arrive in the street, looking for signs of the Wests. After the Wests were arrested, local criminals organised torch-lit tours of the house for up to &#163;500.  <p>  <p>The sign '25 Cromwell Street', which many newspapers used as a logo for the story, is now the subject of a legal argument between members of the West family, some of whom have laid claim to it.  <p>  <p>It was removed by Gloucester police within days of the arrests, because it was feared that a trophy-hunter would take it, and is still held by police. Police were guarding the house last night in case of fresh bounty-seekers. The decision to buy and demolish was supported by all 34 members of the city council. The council leader, Jon Holmes, said: "It is important to erase the physical reminder of these events."  <p>  <p>Councillor Roger Welshman, who has represented the Cromwell Street area for 10 years, said: "It will take some time for the scars to heal." The &#163;40,000 from the sale of the house will go through the Official Solicitor to the West estate, which benefits the surviving children. The four youngest are still in foster homes on the south coast.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
