 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Queen opens new memorial to civil victims of war</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Queen opens new memorial to civil victims of war</b><br><br><br><b><h2>11 October 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Tribute to civil victims of war and tyranny  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>John Ezard</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>A few yards from the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier, the Queen yesterday unveiled a civilian counterpart outside Westminster Abbey, enshrining a multiplicity of worldwide anguish.  The circle of green slate is a Memorial to Innocent Victims of Oppression, Violence and War, a testament to uncountable millions of people, living and dead.  <p>  <p>The unknown soldier's tomb holds the remains of an anonymous serviceman buried symbolically after the 1914-18 war, but no individual body is buried under the new plaque, because the war it marks continues daily. It embodies suffering on a scale before which "language stumbles and falls silent in the face of the horror and the pity", said the Dean of Westminster, Michael Mayne, in his speech of dedication.  <p>  <p>It is expected to become a site of pilgrimage, meditation and wreath-laying after great tragedies like Dunblane. It has been placed in the abbey courtyard so visitors of other faiths can use it.  <p>  <p>Its diversity was reflected in the make-up of the procession of 12 representative victims with whom the Queen and the Duke of Edinburgh walked to the plaque.  <p>  <p>They included a Dunblane teacher; a blind, handless Bosnian youth; a former Belsen inmate; a Palestinian; the widow of a jailed Burmese MP; survivors of the 1915 Armenian massacre and the 1994 Rwanda genocide; Irina Ratushinskaya, the poet imprisoned in the Soviet Union; and Joan Wilson, mother of Marie, who was killed in the Enniskillen bombing.  <p>  <p>Traffic came to a halt and passers-by thronged as the grieving cavalcade emerged into the abbey courtyard.  <p>  <p>The Dean said that the soldier's tomb was the abbey's most potent grave, but the new stone was no less eloquent.  <p>  <p>"It seeks to broaden our understanding of what has been done - and is being done daily - in this bloodiest of centuries to those who are our brothers and our sisters and whose blood, like that of Abel, cries out to us from the ground.  <p>  <p>"This new stone speaks for those who have been in the way of invading armies, pawns in a thousand messy wars."  <p>  <p>The plaque has been a long-nurtured project for the Dean, who is on the verge of retirement. In yesterday's address, he said he had no easy answers to civilian suffering. But the service he drafted was forthright in two ways. It included British street children in its definition of victims. And one of its prayers made the 600-strong congregation promise to "strive to resist the wilful - or thoughtless - creation of poverty".  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
