 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Recluse leaves &#163;1.3m</TITLE></HEAD> <body  bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right  BORDER="0"></A> <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br>
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Recluse  leaves £1.3m</b><br><br><br><b><h2>15 October  1996</h2></b><br><h2>Ragged-trousered philanthropist bequeaths &#163;1.3m  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Nick Varley</b><br><br>      <p> <p>A recluse nicknamed Compo after the scruff in the TV series, 'Last of the  Summer Wine', has stunned his neighbours by leaving &#163;1.3m in his will to  charity. <p> <p>Arthur McCullagh, aged 74, dressed like a tramp - with a piece of  rope for a belt - and lived alone in a house described as "very basic indeed" in  the village of Wool, Dorset. <p> <p>He once sewed up a gash above his eye rather  than visit hospital. But he saved his greatest surprise until after his death of  heart failure in June. He left &#163;20,000 to the parish council - the  equivalent of an entire year's local tax levy - and the remainder of his estate,  &#163;1,295,399, to four national charities. <p> <p>Neighbours could not believe  that the familar figure in Wellington boots and an old jacket with the pockets  torn off had been a millionaire. One, Alan Brown, said: "He was a very kind and  gentle chap, and everyone liked him, but we all assumed he was really poor. <p>  <p>"He created cars by putting fibreglass shells over old engines and chassis  because it was cheaper. His wealth has come as a shock to people. They thought he  was poverty-stricken. By the way he dressed most people thought he was a  gardener." Joan Dominy, aged 64, who knew Mr McCullagh for 14 years, added: "He  was an amazing character - a real eccentric - but he had a wonderful sense of  humour. "He made everything himself, and he would not spend a penny if he could  make something himself which would do the same job." <p> <p>Much of Mr  McCullagh's wealth is thought to have come from his parents, with whom he lived  until they died, and his grandparents. <p> <p>He was an only child. He married in  the Sixties but his wife died of cancer in 1981, childless. The bulk of his money  will be split between the Brook Hospital for Animals, the Marie Curie Memorial  Fund, Help the Aged and the British Heart Foundation. <p> <p>The village is  likely to put its share of the money into bricks and mortar: a new meeting and  sports hall. <p> <p>The parish clerk, Rod Webb, said: "If we do build something  with Mr McCullagh's money, we will name it after him." <p> <p> <p> <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr> <td  align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG  border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=center valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=right valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2ob