 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Clare Short reunited with  son</TITLE></HEAD> <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000"  alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea"> <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br>
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Clare Short reunited with  son</b><br><br><br><b><h2>17 October 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Clare Short and son  reunited</h2><h3>Blair delighted as frontbencher announces she and the boy she gave for  adoption 31 years ago now "both feel complete"  </h2>
 <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Michael  White</b><br><br>      <p> <p>Clare Short, the Labour front bencher, last night astonished and delighted  her colleagues by announcing that she had been reunited with the son she gave  away when she was a young student 31 years ago. <p> <p>Ms Short and her son, City  lawyer Toby Graham, said in a statement issued through the Labour Party  yesterday: "We are at the moment happier than we have been in our lives. It is  more wonderful than anyone can imagine and makes us both feel complete. It is  like falling in love, but less complicated. And it is guaranteed to last forever." <p> <p>To add party political stardust to a genuine, tear-jerking story,  it emerged that Mr Graham was raised in what was described as a Tory background.  "He says he was a One Nation Tory and that he was already being won over to the  ideas of Tony Blair before he knew about Clare," the statement said. The shadow  overseas aid spokesman, better known as the passionate leftwing conscience within  Mr Blair's shadow cabinet, revealed what had not been known to the Labour  hierarchy until recently: that when she married as an 18-year-old student in 1964  she was pregnant - and soon decided it would be best to have her baby adopted.  <p> <p>As the Labour leader, who this week extolled the virtues of traditional  family values, expressed his delight at the reunion - "I wish them the very best  of happiness" - Labour officials explained that 50-year-old Ms Short, descendant  of staunch Irish republicans from Crossmaglen, had acted as a Catholic teenager  would easily have done in the early Sixties. Soon she and her then-husband, Andy  Moss, who were divorced in 1974, "deeply regretted what they had done". The  decision made it difficult for the marriage to work. "Since that time, Clare has  lived with a sense of pain and loss at the centre of her life." <p> <p>Mother and  son appealed for privacy, though they will appear for photographers at  Westminster this morning. <p> <p>Mr Graham was said to have started a search for  his real mother after the birth of his own daughters, now aged 18 months and 2  and three quarters, and learned a year ago who she was. He did not initially realise Ms Short  was a well-known MP. <p> <p>Mr Blair has known for some time of the relationship.  The MP decided to go public with it because knowledge of her son was becoming  widely known. It was first reported on ITN last night. <p> <p>In 1981 Ms Short,  then a civil servant, married Alex Lyon, a radical Labour MP who had been sacked  as a Home Office minister. He died after a long illness last year. The couple had  no children, but Ms Short's career flourished. <p> <p>She won Birmingham Ladywood  in 1983, the year Mr Lyon lost York. She rose to NEC and shadow cabinet rank -  although her progress was punctuated by rows and resignations. <p> <p>This summer  she complained that Mr Blair was surrounded by "people who live in the dark", a  typically blunt assessment of the leader's entourage. But Mr Blair last night put  bygones behind him. He declared: "I am thrilled for Clare that she has met her  son and that they have been able to form such a warm relationship... Clare  will be a marvellous grandmother to his children." <p> <p>The nearest comparable  revalation for a high-flying woman MP was the discovery that Virginia Bottomley,  was pregnant with her eldest child when she married her husband, Peter, when she  was 19. <p> <p>The emergence of more women into prominent positions in public  life since the Sixties makes it inevitable that such family traumas will emerge.  Until recently many women who chose to make politics a career remained unmarried  or childless unless - like Margaret Thatcher - they were married to wealthy men  who could support them and pay for child care. Even that option exacted a price  and Lady Thatcher's daughter, Carol, recently wrote a memoir of her father, in  which she revealed the future prime minister to be a self-absorbed career woman  who devoted what parental energy she had to her son, Carol's twin, Mark. <p>  <p>In his statement, Mr Blair said: "Clare first told me of their situation some  time ago, after her son approached her. I fully accept that Clare is a well-known  public figure, but I hope the media will be sensitive in their approaches to the  other people involved." <p> <p>Ms Short and Mr Graham, now 31, revealed that she  gave birth while she was a student, but gave her son up for adoption after six  weeks. The baby was adopted by John Graham, director of a public company, and his  wife, who brought him up in a comfortably-off Conservative family. <p> <p>He was  sent to a boarding school, studied law at the University of East Anglia and is  now a solicitor in the City. <p> <p>When the adoption law allowing children to  trace their real mothers changed, Ms Short had said that if her son tried to  trace her, she was willing to meet him. <p> <p>Four weeks ago, the pair met for  the first time in 30 years. In an interview in the Independent newspaper the MP  said: "It was just that this big thing at the centre of my life was painful. Of  course now I feel fabulous. It isn't painful any more." <p> <p>She adds: "I found  out I was pregnant just after my 18th birthday. My first thought was my parents -  you know I come from a Catholic family. It was different times back them.  Everyone was more innocent." <p> <p>A student in Birmingham at the time, she  married the child's father and then contacted an adoption agency. <p> <p>"I just  thought I would never go back to university, that it would be terrible all round,  terrible for the baby, there would be no money, so what I was doing was best for  everyone. When they came to take him it was terrible. It's been terrible  ever since." Mr Graham told the newspaper: "Officially I've been looking for  about a year, but in my mind I always wanted to know and always intended to do  this." <p> <p> <p> <p> <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr> <td  align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG  border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=center valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=right valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td> </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
