 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Wallace and Gromit lost in New  York</TITLE></HEAD> <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000"  alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea"> <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br>
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Wallace and Gromit lost  in New York</b><br><br><br><b><h2>21 October 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Wallace and Gromit lost in New York  </h2>
 <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Ian Katz</b><br><br>      <p> <p>Wallace and Gromit were missing in New York yesterday after being  accidentally left in the boot of a taxi. <p> <p>The original plasticine models of  the characters that won Nick Park three Academy Awards were lost shortly after  the film-maker arrived on Saturday for a promotional tour. <p> <p>Yesterday a  distraught Mr Park was appealing on local radio stations for help in finding  them. "He feels like he's lost two pals," said his publicist, Arthur Sheriff.  "These are the only ones, it's not as if there's a duplicate set." <p> <p>He said  Wallace and Gromit, together with their motorcycle and sidecar, were put in the  boot of a taxi for the journey from JFK airport to a Manhattan hotel. Because it  was raining heavily, Mr Sheriff and Mr Park took cover under the hotel canopy  while a porter unloaded their bags. <p> <p>"Nick then realised the porter hadn't  taken Wallace and Gromit out - but by then the cab had left," he said. Mr Park  gave chase but "by then every cab had turned into 100 cabs". <p> <p>The models  were used in Mr Park's most recent film, 'Close Shave'. The motorcycle and sidecar  cost &#163;4,000 to build, but Mr Sheriff said the value of Wallace and Gromit  was "incalculable". <p> <p> <p> <p> <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr> <td  width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif"  ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr> <td  align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG  border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=center valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=right valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td> </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
