 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Matthew Harding dies in helicopter  crash</TITLE></HEAD> <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000"  alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea"> <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br>
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Matthew Harding dies in  helicopter crash</b><br><br><br><b><h2>24 October 1996</h2></b><br><h2>'Goodbye,  Mr Chelsea'</h2><h3>Matthew Harding's legacy will live on in football  </h2>
 <br>By 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>John Duncan</b><br><br>      <p> <p>He wasn't a politician, a world leader, or even a great sportsman. He was  a businessman, a large investor in a football club and a supporter. But the  fanfare to the Chelsea vice-chairman, Matthew Harding, killed in a helicopter  crash in Cheshire late on Tuesday as he returned from watching his team play,  straddled all those worlds. Tributes flowed at Stamford Bridge, Chelsea's  stadium. <p> <p>"I was shocked by the news of Matthew's tragic death," said the  Prime Minister, John Major, a fellow Chelsea fan. "Chelsea was his passion and he  did a huge amount to help the club he loved." <p> <p>Chelsea said its north  stand, which Mr Harding's money helped build, will be named after him. There will  be a minute's silence before Premier League matches this weekend. <p> <p>"He was  so full of life and vigour and someone deeply committed to his country," said the  Labour leader Tony Blair. Last month, Mr Harding announced he was donating  &#163;1m to Labour. But it is thought only about half the money had already been  paid. <p> <p>The England coach, Glenn Hoddle, said: "It is unbelievable the game  should lose somebody who had so much to offer so young and in such  circumstances." Chelsea's manager, Ruud Gullit, said: "He was a guy who wanted to  be a player also, one of us. He was more like a supporter really than a  director." <p> <p>Mr Harding's death, at 42, touched the high and the low among  Chelsea's support: yesterday's impromptu memorial at Stamford Bridge contained  one floral tribute from the notorious hooligan gang the Headhunters, as well as  hundreds of touching wreaths. "Goodbye, Mr Chelsea," said one. The accident,  which claimed five lives, occurred in Middlewich at around 11pm on Tuesday as the  helicopter carried Mr Harding's party back from Chelsea's game at Bolton. Mr  Blair had used the same aircraft after last month's Blackpool conference. <p>  <p>Witnesses suggested engine failure. The wreckage of the French-built  helicopter will be examined by the Civil Aviation Authority. "It was the dead of  night and I could hear it very well," said Josephine Horrocks, aged 43, who lives  half a mile from the crash site. "The engine was faltering. All of a sudden there  was a massive bang." <p> <p>The first clue to the identity of those who died came  when rescue workers found the burned remnants of a match programme. <p> <p>Mr  Harding, estranged from his wife, Ruth, with whom he had four children, had a  two-year-old daughter, Ella, to his girlfriend, Vicky Jaramillo, aged 25. <p>  <p>He made his fortune in insurance, rising from office junior to chairman of the  profitable Benfield Group, and amassing &#163;170m. He ploughed &#163;25m into  Chelsea. <p> <p>"Mr Harding's financial commitment to the club is in place and  will not be jeopardised by his death," said Chelsea's chairman, Ken Bates. "His  memory is best served by achieving the objectives that he set for the club - in  achieving his dream of a world-class team in a world-class stadium." The other  victims of the crash were the pilot, Michael Goss, aged 38, journalist John  Bauldie, aged 47, and two executives of Benfield companies, Tony Burridge, aged  39, and Raymond Deane, aged 43. Kate Alderson, 28, a Times journalist attending  the scene, died in a car crash. <p> <p> <p> <p> <br><br><center><TABLE  border=0><tr> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG  SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td> <td width=40><A  HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT  BORDER="0"></A></td> </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400  border=0><tr> <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A  HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=center valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td> <td align=right valign=middle  width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0   SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td> </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
