 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Rikki Neave's mother sentenced to seven years but cleared of murder</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Rikki Neave's mother sentenced to seven years but cleared of murder</b><br><br><br><b><h2>31 October 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Mother cleared of Rikki's murder  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Christopher Elliott</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>Ministers last night ordered a team of social service inspectors to carry out a thorough review of Cambridgeshire's child protection practice following the death of Rikki Neave, whose mother Ruth was yesterday cleared of his murder. Two social workers in Peterborough were also suspended last night.  <p>  <p>Neave, aged 28, was unanimously acquitted yesterday of her six-year-old son's murder and manslaughter, but was jailed for seven years after admitting cruelty to three of her four children, including Rikki, who was on the at-risk register when his body was found in a wood near his Peterborough home in November 1994. Because Neave has spent 18 months locked up on remand she could be released within two years.  <p>  <p>Her children were beaten, burned with cigarettes and thrown across rooms over a period of six years.  <p>  <p>Simon Burns, the health minister, said last night that he was very concerned at the case. While Cambridgeshire had carried out its own internal review, and had commissioned an independent report from the Bridge Child Care Development Service, he was sending in inspectors to be doubly sure. Trevor Harvey, Rikki's father, and former partner of Ruth, last night called for a public inquiry. In a statement with other members of the family, he criticised Cambridgeshire social workers' care of his son.  <p>  <p>Sandra Chesney, Rikki's aunt, said: "This terrible tragedy could have been avoided if the professionals involved carried out their duties to the standards expected of them."  <p>  <p>Since Rikki's death, evidence has emerged of a social services department riven with disputes between staff and management, and with poor morale and a heavy caseload. It is understood that the investigation by the social services' inspectorate will focus on management failures to gather evidence of the childrens' ordeal and act decisively.  <p>  <p>The county council last night admitted in a statement that mistakes had been made.  <p>  <p>Ted Unsworth, director designate of the county's social services department, said that with hindsight the department had persisted far too long in trying to keep the family together: "We didn't establish a comprehensive picture of what life was like in the Neave household."  <p>  <p>Sentencing Neave, Mr Justice Popplewell said she was inadequate and wholly unfit to be a mother. "I have rarely come across a case of such systematic and persistent cruelty to young children."  <p>  <p>Outlining the cruelty charges, Christopher Metcalfe said that examples of the brutality included Mrs Neave stubbing cigarettes out in the palms of two of the children's hands, repeatedly kicking one of the daughters in the spine and often locking them out late at night. She pulled one child's hair so hard the scalp bled, then hit the child over the head with a hairbrush and broke it in two. On another occasion, Neave squeezed a washing up liquid bottle into Rikki's mouth.  <p>  <p>Neave's pleas of guilty to five specimen charges of cruelty spanning six years, as well as to one of burglary and another of supplying amphetamines, were kept from the jury during the four week trial at Northampton crown court.  <p>  <p>The prosecution had alleged that Neave had murdered Rikki as a human sacrifice to win back her husband Dean, who was not Rikki's father and did not get on with the boy.  <p>  <p>On the morning of Rikki's death, Neave said he had gone off to school and she never saw him again. She reported him missing at 6pm.  <p>  <p>The prosecution alleged he had gone home to tea, after playing truant, and Neave strangled him, washed the body and laid him out in a copse in a manner similar to that of Leonardo da Vinci's drawing of the 'Vitruvian Man'. Neave, who was brought up in care and was diagnosed as having a personality disorder as a teenager, always denied strangling him.  <p>  <p>Meanwhile, police are investigating the death of another toddler whose family was also known to Peterborough East social workers.  <p>  <p>Neave, who collapsed in tears when the not guilty verdicts were read out, said through her solicitors she hoped police would redouble their efforts to find "the true killers". "Many who live near me were quick to condemn me without having heard a word of evidence. I have had to wait for the moment now to be able to say I am not guilty of killing my own child."   <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
