 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Furore over Allan Starkie's book about the Duchess of York</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Furore over Allan Starkie's book about the Duchess of York</b><br><br><br><b><h2>2 November 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Duchess of York denies book's suicide claim  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Owen Bowcott</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>The furore over the Duchess of York's tangled private life flared up again yesterday amid claims she would have committed suicide but for her young daughters.  <p>  <p>The claims are contained in 'Fergie: Her Secret Life' by the former confidant of the duchess Dr Allan Starkie. Extracts are published in the Daily Mail this week.  <p>  <p>Dr Starkie, a friend of her former 'financial adviser' John Bryan, recalls her comment: "If it weren't for the children the only answer would be to kill myself."  <p>  <p>The duchess was reported to have been distraught over her soaring overdraft and the emotional struggle between Mr Bryan and her husband, Prince Andrew. The book describes how she turned into "a woman no longer quite in control" and became "driven by fear and lust".  <p>  <p>The Daily Mail says Dr Starkie kept a copious diary, and the duchess once told him: "One day you'll write such a marvellous book about it." Earlier this year the duchess attempted to halt the book's publication with an injunction. Four weeks ago she dropped the action after she was ordered to pay &#163;500,000 into court in case she lost the case.  <p>  <p>After her lawsuit collapsed, the duchess was said to have telephoned the New York Times to deny 'vicious rumours' that the Queen considered her a suicide risk.  <p>  <p>Her spokesman, Howard Rubinstein, said yesterday: "I don't think the Duchess of York ever said anything about killing herself. It was patently the last thing on her mind. It's ridiculous."  <p>  <p>The Duchess of York's own autobiography 'My Story', is due out on 14 November . Hello! magazine yesterday confirmed it had bought serialisation rights and would run extracts next week.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
