 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Stephen Dorrell wins extra cash for NHS</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Stephen Dorrell wins extra cash for NHS</b><br><br><br><b><h2>15 November 1996</h2></b><br><h2>NHS trusts miss financial targets as executive pay rises  </h2>
  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David Brindle</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>More than half all NHS trusts last year failed in their duty to achieve their financial targets and almost one in five returned a deficit, figures released today show.  <p>  <p>The number of trust chief executives paid more than &#163;100,000 nevertheless rose from 10 to 19. Their average remuneration was &#163;71,400, an increase of 3.5 per cent on the 1994/95 financial year. The figures, from the Healthcare Financial Management Association (HFMA), part of the Chartered Institute of Public Finance and Accountancy, follow more evidence of NHS funding problems. Doctors in Exeter said yesterday that 2,700 patients due operations before next April would have to wait until the new financial year because the Royal Devon and Exeter hospital had to cancel 20 weekly operating lists.  <p>  <p>Stephen Dorrell, the Health Secretary, yesterday told a meeting organised by the National Association of Health Authorities and Trusts that despite the &#163;500m rumoured to be won for the NHS in the Budget, 'the problems won't go away'.  <p>  <p>The HFMA figures, from more than 90 per cent of trusts in England, show that 210 of 372 supplying figures for 1995/96 failed to meet the requirement that they achieve a 6 per cent rate of return on their assets.  <p>  <p>Of 386 trusts supplying profit-and-loss figures, 71 (18 per cent) recorded a deficit in breach a further requirement to break even.  <p>  <p>In 1994/95, 77 per cent of trusts achieved the six per cent rate of return and only eight per cent reported a deficit.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
