 <HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Guardian Year - Boris Yeltsin undergoes heart bypass operation</TITLE></HEAD>  <body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#ff0000" alink="#adeaea" vlink="#adeaea">  <A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/stitle.gif" ALIGN=right BORDER="0"></A>  <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><blockquote><br><br> 
<!--INFOLINE--><b>Boris Yeltsin undergoes heart bypass operation</b><br><br><br><b><h2>6 November 1996</h2></b><br><h2>Meanwhile in Moscow, Yeltsin lies in intensive care</h2><h3>Five bypasses reveal more serious damage to president's heart  </h3>  <br>By
<!--INFOLINE--><b>David Hearst</b><br><br>      <p>  <p>A critical 48 hours will decide the success of President Boris Yeltsin's bypass operation as doctors monitor his progress after seven hours of surgery constructing five heart bypasses.  <p>  <p>Later today his international team of surgeons will decide whether to take the 65-year-old off an artificial respirator to see if he can breathe unaided. The surgery uncovered a much more badly diseased heart than had previously been thought.  <p>  <p>Renat Akchurin, the surgeon who led the medical team, said yesterday's operation was a success. After grafting a number of veins on to the arteries around the heart, he said all indications were that the heart was getting enough blood to function normally.  <p>  <p>"I was trying to forget that it was the president of Russia and think this is an ordinary patient."  <p>  <p>George Noon, an American surgeon and one of the advisers to the Russian team, said Mr Yeltsin had five bypasses which should not affect his chances of a full recovery.  <p>  <p>"It was very standard and everything went in a very routine manner without complications," he said. He added that a couple of Mr Yeltsin's arteries had sections which were completely blocked.  <p>  <p>Mr Yeltsin regained consciousness clearing one of the hurdles on his path to recovery. His doctors, helped by specialists from Germany, will have a clearer picture when the artificial ventilation is turned off this morning. Tony Rickard, a cardiologist at London's Royal Brompton Hospital, said: "There are a number of key milestones President Yeltsin has got to pass. He has passed one of them - and that is that his own heart has taken over from the artificial heart that was used during the operation."  <p>  <p>Michael DeBakey, the pioneering American heart surgeon, said the operation was a complete success. "President Yeltsin will be able to return to his office and carry out his duties in normal fashion," he said. Yevgeny Chazov, who kept three Soviet leaders alive in the 1970s and 1980s, said: "The operation went better than I expected." He said Mr Yeltsin's heart had been stopped for 68 minutes while surgeons grafted veins. However, some medical experts said the greater than expected number of bypasses showed Mr Yeltsin's heart was more badly diseased than previously thought. "If you say you're going to do three or four bypasses and you do more, you've found more problems than you expected," said John Wright, head of cardiac services at the London Chest Hospital.  <p>  <p>It started in tight secrecy yesterday when Russia woke up to the news that Mr Yeltsin had formally handed over all his powers, including control of the nuclear button, to the prime minister, Viktor Chernomyrdin.  <p>  <p>Mr Yeltsin said in an address read out by his press secretary, Sergei Yastrzhembsky: "Not for a minute will the country be without a leader with full powers."  <p>  <p>All attention will focus on how long Mr Yeltsin leaves power in Mr Chernomyrdin's hands. The powers he transferred to his prime minister will be resumed by the signing of a another decree. But only Mr Yeltsin will decide when.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>  <p>GDN 11 Nov 96 Yeltsin is 'out of the woods' (170)   <p>  <p>President Boris Yeltsin is likely to be discharged in about 10 days from the hospital where he is recovering from quintuple heart bypass surgery, the Kremlin doctor, Sergei Mironov, said yesterday. He told Russian television that Mr Yeltsin would finish recuperating at his country residence in Barvikha, outside Moscow.  <p>  <p>The president's daughters, Tatyana Dyachenko and Yelena Okulov, told the independent station NTV last night that Mr Yeltsin was doing well, but had little appetite and was still in some pain. Dr Mironov said Mr Yeltsin was spending several hours a day sitting up, and was walking around his suite at the Kremlin hospital.  <p>  <p>Michael DeBakey, the eminent American cardiologist advising the Russian medical team, said he was flying home to Houston and that Mr Yeltsin was "out of the woods".  <p>  <p>From Bonn, the Itar-Tass news agency reported that one of the German consultants, Axel Haverich, told reporters that the medical team at one point considered a transplant.  <p>  <p>  <p>  <br><br><center><TABLE border=0><tr>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jan.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jandot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/feb.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/febdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/mar.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/mardot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/apr.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/aprdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/may.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/maydot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jun.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/jundot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/jul.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/juldot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/aug.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/augdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/sep.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/sepdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/oct.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/octdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/nov.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/novdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  <td width=40><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/dec.html"><IMG SRC="/g96/pix/decdot.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="0"></A></td>  </tr></TABLE></center><center><TABLE height=30 width=400 border=0><tr>  <td align=left valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/byauthor/autha.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/b2auth.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=center valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/index.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="/g96/pix/g96.gif"></A></h2></td>  <td align=right valign=middle width=200><h2><A HREF="/g96/bymonth/Obitjan.html"><IMG border=0  SRC="/g96/pix/b2obit.gif"></A></h2></td>  </tr></table></center></BODY></HTML> 
