	The plans of BBC director general John Birt to reorganise the prestigious World Service, merging its news operation with the Corporation's domestic radio output, have been greeted with outrage and deep concern.<br>

      For 120 million weekly listeners around the globe, the BBC World Service offers an unrivalled source of information and has gained worldwide respect for its standards of excellence. <A HREF="london.html"><IMG SRC="pix/arrow.gif" ALT="" VALIGN=BOTTOM border=0></A> <B>Full story</B><br>
 

     
