<!--TOP-->
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="550">
<TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="/pix/edupix/education.gif" ALT="The Guardian Education" BORDER="0"></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P><br>
<!--INTRO COPY-->

<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="20" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="550">
<TR><TD>
	The Guardian's education site provides an extra dimension
to the paper's daily news coverage and the background features in our Education
and Higher Education supplements on Tuesdays. It hosts electronic debates on
the big issues affecting schools and universities. It gives a platform for the
best student writers. It provides parents and teachers with resource material
to help explain the stories behind the news. And it offers an accessible
presentation of key data on the performance of secondary schools and
universities. Read the arguments. Join the debates.
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>


