<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Astronomy for the Jet Set
</TITLE>

<META name="description" content=
	"This Observatorium Exhibit highlights airborne astronomy and
why we do it.  The exhibit also describes the Kuiper Airborne
Observatory and the planning NASA SOFIA Observatory.">

<META name="keywords" content=
	"airborne astronomy, infrared radiation, Kuiper Airborne
Observatory, KAO, Stratospheric Observatory for Infrared Astronomy,
SOFIA, NASA IITA">

</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/observe/exhibit/space/sofia/graphics/background.jpg"
TEXT="000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#0000FF">

<TABLE WIDTH="100%">

<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="graphics/clear.gif"></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER>

<IMG SRC="/observe/exhibit/space/sofia/graphics/final_header.jpg">
<BR>


<FONT COLOR="FF0000"><H1><B>Astronomy for the Jet Set -- <BR>
Telescopes on Airplanes</H1></B></FONT>

<BR>

<P>Airplanes can be nasty places for sensitive and delicate 
passengers, especially when those passengers are telescopes!  
The pain is worth the gain, though, as you will see.  

<P>SOFIA will be NASA's newest airborne astronomical observatory.  It will
consist of a telescope more than 8 feet (2.5 meters) in diameter housed in
a Boeing 747.  It will observe the heavens from above 40,000 feet (12,000 
meters). 

<P>So what will it be: coffee, tea, or Milky Way?

</CENTER>

<H2>Contents
</H2>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="sofia_1.html">Why Do Astronomy From an Aircraft?</A>
<LI><A HREF="sofia_2.html">Short History of Airborne Astronomy</A>
<LI><A HREF="sofia_3.html">SOFIA -- NASA's Newest Airborne Observatory</A>
<LI><A HREF="sofia_4.html">SOFIA -- Science and Other Uses</A>
<LI><A HREF="sofia_ref.html">More Info at Other WWW Sites</A>
</UL>

<HR>

<CENTER> 

<A HREF="/observe/exhibit/exhibit.html">
<IMG  BORDER="0" SRC="/observe/exhibit/space/sofia/graphics/exit_btn.gif" 
ALT="[EXIT]"></A>

<A HREF="sofia_1.html">
<IMG BORDER="0" SRC="/observe/exhibit/space/sofia/graphics/r_btn.gif" 
ALT="[FORWARD]"></A>

<BR>

</CENTER>

<HR>

<!--#include virtual="/observe/includes/footer.html"-->

</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

