<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Observatorium - Tools and Data</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<CENTER>

<IMG SRC="/observe/graphics/tools_header.gif" ALT="NASA's Observatorium">

<BR>
<A HREF="/observe/graphics/buttonb.map">
<IMG BORDER="0" SRC="/observe/graphics/buttonb.gif"
ALT="Navigation Links" ISMAP></A>
</CENTER>

<CENTER>
<H1>You Can Do Remote Sensing</H1>
</CENTER>

<P>It's not magic.  All it takes is a basic understanding of the
underlying concepts, the right tools, and the data itself.  We have
tried to cover the conceptual aspects elsewhere in this site,
especially in the <A
HREF="/observe/exhibit/reference/module/main.html">reference
section</A>.  In this section, we provide information on where to
obtain remote sensing data and the tools necessary to display,
manipulate, and analyze those data.</P>


<CENTER>
<A HREF="stepby/multi.html">
<IMG BORDER="0" SRC="graphics/free.gif"
ALT="Free Software"></A>
</CENTER>

<TABLE WIDTH="100%" CELLPADDING="5">

<TR>

<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<A HREF="stepby/multi.html">
<IMG BORDER="0" SRC="graphics/set.gif"
ALT="Dataset image"></A>
</TD>

<TD VALIGN="TOP"> 
<P>Yes, I said free.  We have seven-band, 512x512, 30 meter resolution
data sets from the Landsat Thematic Mapper and a step-by-step
procedure for viewing and analyzing them using a freeware application
that is available for both Macintosh and PC computers.  Download the
images and the software and you can be doing remote sensing today!</P>
</TD>

</TR>

</TABLE>

<CENTER>
<A HREF="sources_data.html">
<IMG BORDER="0" SRC="graphics/data.gif"
ALT="Sources of Remote Sensing Data"></A>
</CENTER>

<TABLE WIDTH="100%" CELLPADDING="5">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<A HREF="sources_data.html">
<IMG BORDER="0" SRC="graphics/sat.gif"
ALT="Satellite image"></A>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P>Remote sensing satellites have been collecting observations of the
earth and space for many years.  There are several major NASA and
other government archives of earth and space data.  There are also several
commercial remote sensing firms that offer value-added products.</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<CENTER>
<A HREF="sources_sw.html">
<IMG BORDER="0" SRC="graphics/soft.gif" 
ALT="Sources of Remote Sensing Software"></A>
</CENTER>

<TABLE WIDTH="100%" CELLPADDING="5">

<TR>

<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<A HREF="sources_sw.html">
<IMG BORDER="0" SRC="graphics/source.gif"
ALT="Disks"></A>
</TD>

<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P>Remote sensing display and analysis software is now available for
almost every type of computer system, including those found in homes
and schools.  We have included summaries of a few popular packages,
both commercial and in the public domain, as well as links to where to
obtain more information and the actual software.</P>
</TD>

</TR>

