<HEAD>
<TITLE>Observatorium - About RSPAC</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF"> 

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/observe/graphics/head_bar.gif" ALIGN="top">

<BR><BR>

<H1>About The Observatorium</H1>

<IMG SRC="graphics/nasa_logo.gif" ALT="NASA Logo">
<IMG SRC="graphics/bdm_logo.gif" ALT="BDM Logo">
<IMG SRC="graphics/wvu_logo.gif" ALT="WVU Logo">

</CENTER>

<P>The Observatorium is a project of the Remote Sensing Public Access
Center (RSPAC).  The RSPAC is a cooperative program among the NASA
Office of Aeronautics <a 
href="/cgi-bin/log.pl?http://quest.arc.nasa.gov/IITA/iita1.html">Information 
Infrastructure Technology and Applications (IITA)</A> Program, <A 
HREF="/cgi-bin/log.pl?http://www.bdm.com">BDM 
International</A>, and <A HREF="/cgi-bin/log.pl?http://www.wvu.edu">West Virginia 
University</A>. The RSPAC is 
located at the NASA Software Independent Verification and Validation 
Center in Fairmont, West Virginia.</P>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#MISSION">The RSPAC Mission</A>
<LI><a href="#PURPOSE">The Observatorium Public Web Server Purpose</a>
<LI><A HREF="#PRESS">Press Releases Related to RSPAC</A>
<LI><A HREF="#CONTACT">Contacting RSPAC</A>
<LI><A HREF="server.html">About Our Server</A>
</UL>

<A NAME="MISSION"><HR></A>
<center><H2>The RSPAC Mission</H2></center>
<p>The purpose of RSPAC is to support and stimulate broad public use,
via the Internet, of the very large remote sensing databases maintained
by NASA and other agencies to stimulate U.S. economic growth, improve
the quality of life, and contribute to the implementation of a 
National Information Infrastructure (NII).  The acceleration of the 
implementation of an NII is a goal of the <A HREF="/cgi-bin/log.pl?http://cesdis.gsfc.nasa.gov/hpccm/hpcc.nasa.html">
High Performance Computing and Communications</A> (HPCC) 
Office of the NASA Office of Aeronautics.</p>

<h3>Specific goals of RSPAC include:</h3>
<UL>
<LI>Extend the dissemination of NASA's large earth and space science 
remote sensing databases by improving public access capabilities to reach
a broader user community.
<P></P>
<LI>Showcase and support the development of technologies and applications 
that will stimulate effective use of NASA's remote sensing data, leading
to gains in education, quality of life, and economic growth.
<P></P>
<LI>Expedite the development of digital library technologies for support
of remote sensing data applications by providing a stable and reliable 
test bed facility.
<P></P>
<LI>Provide high quality training and assistance to individuals and 
organizations accessing NASA data.
</UL>
<BR><BR>

<A NAME="PURPOSE"><HR></A>

<CENTER>
<H2>The Observatorium Public Web Server Purpose</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>Our purpose in providing a public information server is to promote
improved public access to NASA's large repository of earth and space
science data, applications, and technologies.  We will focus on meeting
the information needs of non-traditional or under-served users in the
general public.  Specifically, we will: </P>

<UL>
<LI>Help users learn about earth and space science.

<BR><BR>
<LI>Showcase developing projects of the NASA Cooperative Agreement Teams (CATs).

<BR><BR>
<LI>Provide data and information related to the NASA Information 
Infrastructure Technology and Applications (IITA) program.

<BR><BR>
<LI>Help users access and participate in the ongoing efforts of the 
NASA CATs and IITA programs.

<BR><BR>
<LI>Provide information about technologies and developments 
related to the National Information Infrastructure 
(NII) initiative and the Internet.

<BR><BR>
<LI>Help users learn about other related NASA and Internet resources.
</UL>

<P>We will provide information content that is clear, concise,
educational, and entertaining.  It will assume users are looking for
information, but may not possess specialized knowledge. </P>

<A NAME="PRESS"><HR></A>

<CENTER>
<H2>Press Releases</H2>
</CENTER>

<UL>
<LI>Read the NASA press release about <A HREF="abt_bdm.html">RSPAC</A>.
<BR><BR>

<LI>Read the NASA press release about <A HREF="abt_apps.html">remote 
sensing database applications and digital library technologies</A>. 
<BR><BR>

<LI>Read the NASA press release about <A HREF="abt_grnt.html">public use 
of earth and space science data over the Internet</A>.
<BR><BR>

</UL>

<A NAME="CONTACT"><HR></A>


