<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Observatorium - Flood Exhibit</TITLE>

<META name="description" content=
	"This Observatorium Exhibit desribes how remote sensing data
was used in the '93 Mississippi flood to identify areas for
evacuation.  It has a cool .gif animation sequence.">

<META name="keywords" content=
	"Mississippi, flood, 1993, 93, '93, River Des Peres,
St. Louis, Community Development Agency, remote sensing, disaster
assistance, disaster recovery, emergency management, emergency
planning, evacuation, .gif animation, NASA IITA">

</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="graphics/map.gif">

<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="/observe/exhibit/graphics/final-header.gif" 
ALT="[header-logo]" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<BR>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="graphics/montage.gif" WIDTH="432" HEIGHT="180" ALIGN="BOTTOM" 
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" ALT="[Flood logo]">
<BR>
<BR>

Lee Blackmore was finally enjoying an early morning cup of coffee when the
phone rang. A young image analyst and GIS specialist with the St.  Louis
Community Development Agency (CDA), he had finally managed to grab a
few hours of sleep after nearly two days in front of his computer
producing maps and images of the flooded Mississippi River. On the phone
was an emergency coordinator from the police department. &quot;Lee,&quot; the
voice said, &quot;we need your help.&quot; 

<BR>
<BR>

