<HEAD>

<TITLE>Earth -- The Ever-Changing Planet</TITLE>

<META name="description" content=
	"This Observatorium Exhibit examines the changes that our
earth experiences and how things like ocean wave heights, hurricanes,
and urbanization can be monitored through the use of remote sensing.">

<META name="keywords" content=
	"earth, ocean, wave height, TOPEX/Poseidon, earth at night, US
U.S. at night, europe at night, japan at night, middle east at night,
DMSP, hurricane, hurricane season, Rice University, Houston Museum of
Natural Science, NASA IITA">

</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="graphics/sky.gif">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/observe/exhibit/earth/rice/graphics/final_header.jpg">
</CENTER>

<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><BR>
<H1>Earth -- The Ever-Changing Planet</H1>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="graphics/world.gif" ALT="spinning 
globe"> </CENTER>
<BR>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP"><BR><IMG SRC="graphics/line.gif" ALT="separator"> <BR>
</TD>
<TD>
<BR>
<P><B><FONT COLOR="006633">Earth -- our home in the universe -- is a 
complex, dynamic, and ever-changing planet.

<P>Walk outside and watch the clouds moving overhead, or a thunderstorm
building up and then unleashing a downpour.  Perhaps you have lived
through a hurricane sweeping onto land from the sea and wreaking havoc on
a community.</P>

<P>Change is unavoidable!</P>

<P>Humans, too, do their share in bringing about change.  If you could
have been an astronaut 100 years ago and looked down on earth from orbit,
you would have seen a world very different from today's. There would have
been few city lights 100 years ago.  The rain forests would have been more 
extensive.</P>

<P>The best place to observe earth's many changes is from space.  Only from 
100 miles up and higher do we get a global view. This exhibit highlights 
some of our planet's changing features from the unique perspective of 
earth orbit.</FONT>
</B>

</TABLE>

<H2>Contents</H2>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="rice_1.html">The Earth at Night -- The Lights Tell Where Most of 
Us Live!</A>
<LI><A HREF="rice_2.html">The 1995 Atlantic Hurricane Season</A>
<LI><A HREF="rice_3.html">Ocean Wave Heights -- 1995</A>
<LI><A HREF="rice_4.html">More Info at other WWW sites</A>
</UL>

<CENTER>
