<H2>Information Search and Retrieval</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>Sometimes the Internet can seem like a library with no card catalog, 
and with all of the books in a big heap in the middle of the floor.  Sure 
there is lots of data there, but who can find anything?</P>

<P>Individual data centers and archives face similar problems.  What 
is the best way to catalog and index large holdings?  How can search 
tools be designed that understand the way people think and ask 
questions?</P> 

<P>The ability to find quickly the information we need and want becomes
more important as the amount of information and number of sites on the
Internet continue to grow.  Here we present some of the work being done to
bring order to the chaos of the Net. </P>

<HR>
<DL>
<B>Universal Spatial Data Access Consortium - GeoScope Project</B>
<DD>
<!--#include
virtual="/observe/techpark/resources/short_abstracts/usdac_short.html"-->
[<A HREF="infodocs/usdac_sh.html">Tell Me More</A>] 
[<A HREF="/cgi-bin/log.pl?http://usdac2.rutgers.edu/">Go There Now</A>]
<BR>
</DL>

<DL>
<DT><B>Retrieval of Digital Images by Means of Content Search</B>
<DD>
<!--#include
virtual="/observe/techpark/resources/short_abstracts/ibm_short.html"-->
[<A HREF="infodocs/ibm_sh.html">Tell Me More</A>]
<BR>
</DL>

<DL>
<P><B>SAIRE - A Scalable Agent-Based Information Retrieval Engine</B>
<DD>
<!--#include
virtual="/observe/techpark/resources/short_abstracts/saire_short.html"-->
[<A HREF="infodocs/saire_sh.html">Tell Me More</A>] 
[<A HREF="/cgi-bin/log.pl?http://saire.ivv.nasa.gov/saire.html">Go There Now</A>] 
<BR>
</DL>

<DL>
<P><B>Project Horizon</B>
<DD>
<!--#include
